WEBVTT

00:03.671 --> 00:05.606
[***]

00:50.684 --> 00:52.086
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:00.828 --> 01:02.596
[***]

01:23.016 --> 01:25.085
Why don't you ride
the bulls, Daddy?

01:25.085 --> 01:27.688
I just ride broncs
bareback, son.

01:27.688 --> 01:28.889
Why?

01:28.889 --> 01:30.458
To tell you the truth,

01:30.458 --> 01:32.326
I'm scared of them.

01:32.326 --> 01:34.495
I ain't scared of 'em.

01:51.812 --> 01:52.980
Hold on tight.

01:52.980 --> 01:54.182
Hold on tight.

01:54.182 --> 01:56.284
Yeah, hold on.

02:03.224 --> 02:04.858
[YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

02:06.694 --> 02:07.661
Good ride, cowboy.

02:26.714 --> 02:28.682
ANNOUNCER:
We're at the
Ardmore Teen Rodeo.

02:28.682 --> 02:31.485
Champions of tomorrow comin'
to you from rodeo arenas.

02:31.485 --> 02:35.256
This is where our youngsters
learn how to cowboy up.

02:35.256 --> 02:36.590
Thanks.

02:36.590 --> 02:39.059
...the guts, the fortitude,
the strength

02:39.059 --> 02:42.430
I'm gonna try, sir.

02:42.430 --> 02:46.200
Right now we're about to watch
Lane Frost.

02:46.200 --> 02:47.768
Now, here's Danny Clyde

02:47.768 --> 02:50.571
who's a five-time National
Finals Rodeo qualifier.

02:50.571 --> 02:52.440
Stay up on your rope.
Yes, sir.

02:52.440 --> 02:54.642
Reach your feet in front.
Yes, sir.

02:54.642 --> 02:56.510
Don't try to second guess him.
I won't.

02:56.510 --> 02:59.079
If you're gonna win, Lane,
you might as well be the best.

02:59.079 --> 03:01.114
Yes, sir.
Bear down.

03:01.114 --> 03:03.484
Yes, sir.
Okay, boys, I'm good.

03:03.484 --> 03:05.686
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

03:05.686 --> 03:07.621
[CROWD CHEERING]

03:14.362 --> 03:15.896
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

03:20.334 --> 03:23.136
ANNOUNCER:
The marking's gonna come up
for this young man

03:23.136 --> 03:25.473
at 86 points.

03:25.473 --> 03:28.242
And you are looking
at your champion rider

03:28.242 --> 03:29.543
of the Ardmore Teen Rodeo.

03:29.543 --> 03:32.313
He cowboyed up
and the judges liked it.

03:32.313 --> 03:34.548
Lane Frost taking
what daddy told him

03:34.548 --> 03:37.351
and putting it to work.
Nice job, cowboy.

03:40.187 --> 03:41.955
[***]

03:48.962 --> 03:51.632
Lane. Come on.

03:51.632 --> 03:53.667
You're gonna be late.

04:03.844 --> 04:06.580
Breakfast is ready.
You got time.

04:06.580 --> 04:08.382
Did you get those
shirts done?

04:08.382 --> 04:11.652
Will you sit down?

04:13.120 --> 04:15.789
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

04:30.904 --> 04:33.541
Lane, I saved you a little money
for you to take.

04:33.541 --> 04:35.676
Oh, Mom, I don't need it,
I've been chopping wood.

04:35.676 --> 04:37.645
Yeah, well, just in case
you get into trouble.

04:37.645 --> 04:39.713
It's not the first time
I've ever been to a rodeo.

04:39.713 --> 04:41.281
True,
but it is the first time

04:41.281 --> 04:43.351
that you have ever rodeoed
with Tuff Hedeman.

04:43.351 --> 04:45.853
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING]

04:57.798 --> 04:58.799
[TURNS OFF STEREO]

04:58.799 --> 05:00.568
[HONKING HORN]

05:02.870 --> 05:05.105
Where in the heck
is that stupid idiot

05:05.105 --> 05:06.340
pencil-neck son of a bitch?

05:06.340 --> 05:08.008
He'll be here.

05:08.008 --> 05:10.744
You know I'm gonna have to drive
like hell to be on time now.

05:10.744 --> 05:13.514
That's the way you drive,
anyway.

05:14.715 --> 05:17.485
Why in the world did I let you
talk me into this?

05:17.485 --> 05:18.719
I like him,

05:18.719 --> 05:21.555
we can use him to help us
share expenses,

05:21.555 --> 05:22.690
and Lane's good.

05:22.690 --> 05:24.024
He ain't that good.

05:24.024 --> 05:26.126
Well, he beat you
at the high school final.

05:26.126 --> 05:28.762
Hey. He got lucky.

05:28.762 --> 05:32.433
He is a puss.
You know it and I know it.

05:32.433 --> 05:34.835
[HONKING HORN]

05:34.835 --> 05:36.904
MAN: Let's go!
Sit down, Lane.

05:36.904 --> 05:39.239
We need you back Monday
or that hay is just gonna rot.

05:39.239 --> 05:40.408
Yes, sir, I will be.

05:40.408 --> 05:42.275
He was out there
at 4:30 this morning.

05:42.275 --> 05:45.145
Nobody ever accused Lane
of trying to get out of work.

05:45.145 --> 05:47.848
A rodeo ain't no way
to make a living, Lane.

05:47.848 --> 05:50.017
You've got to be damn good
to make it pay.

05:50.017 --> 05:52.986
Yes, sir,
that's what I plan on being.

05:52.986 --> 05:54.622
[CAR HORN HONKING]

05:55.556 --> 05:57.958
MAN:
Nice shirt, Lane.

05:59.893 --> 06:01.995
Real pretty.

06:01.995 --> 06:03.631
My mom made it.

06:03.631 --> 06:06.266
Well, you ought to pick
yourself up a whole lot of girls

06:06.266 --> 06:07.501
in that shirt.

06:07.501 --> 06:10.370
I might wanna borrow it
sometime.

06:10.370 --> 06:12.606
Are you ready?

06:12.606 --> 06:14.542
Just waiting on you,
boy.

06:14.542 --> 06:16.176
[TIRES SCREECHING]

06:16.176 --> 06:18.145
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING]

06:23.383 --> 06:26.086
I bet you wish
you were going with him.

06:26.086 --> 06:27.821
[CHUCKLES]

06:27.821 --> 06:30.290
MAN:
You know what? If the shirt
don't get him some girls,

06:30.290 --> 06:31.559
I bet you that stupid hat will.

06:31.559 --> 06:33.226
CODY:
That is an original hat.

06:33.226 --> 06:35.829
LANE:
Is this some kind of joke?
We don't joke in my family.

06:35.829 --> 06:39.332
MAN:
Yeah, well,
we're your family now.

06:39.332 --> 06:42.035
LANE:
Well, this here feather
in my hat's like my trademark.

06:42.035 --> 06:44.137
CODY:
That's what we need, Tuff,
is a trademark.

06:44.137 --> 06:46.139
TUFF:
I got one. It's hard,
full of juice,

06:46.139 --> 06:47.608
and barely fits in my jeans.

06:47.608 --> 06:49.076
LANE:
Geez, Tuff.

06:49.076 --> 06:51.445
TUFF:
It's my flash, Lane.
Cody, want some OJ?

06:51.445 --> 06:53.614
[***]

07:01.054 --> 07:03.724
MAN:
Hey, Lane. I didn't think
you're gonna make it today.

07:03.724 --> 07:05.459
Yeah, you never rode with Tuff.

07:05.459 --> 07:08.428
MAN 2:
Tuff, you drew Bucky Nightmare.
Hang on, he's a rank one.

07:08.428 --> 07:10.197
Good,
that's the kind I like.

07:10.197 --> 07:13.100
ANNOUNCER:
Our last competitor in the
barrel racing competition

07:13.100 --> 07:16.403
today is Kellie Kyle
from Quanah, Texas.

07:16.403 --> 07:19.439
This young lady's already won
over $17,500 this year.

07:19.439 --> 07:21.942
A tremendous performance
this early in the season.

07:21.942 --> 07:23.544
Kellie's no newcomer
to the sport,

07:23.544 --> 07:27.080
she was the National high
school barrel racing champion

07:27.080 --> 07:28.549
back there in 1980.

07:28.549 --> 07:31.318
And she's been riding one of
the fastest Quarter Horses

07:31.318 --> 07:32.786
on the circuit today,

07:32.786 --> 07:35.489
that great Quarter Horse
they call Crawford.

07:37.791 --> 07:40.594
Here they come, the time, 17.3.

07:40.594 --> 07:43.664
That's gonna make her our
Amarillo champion barrel racer.

07:43.664 --> 07:45.298
Now, I expect we'll be
seeing Kellie

07:45.298 --> 07:47.935
at the National Finals Rodeo
in December

07:47.935 --> 07:51.739
as one of our top 15 ladies
in our world standings.

07:51.739 --> 07:53.574
Now, let's get ready
to go down here

07:53.574 --> 07:55.075
with Lane Frost from Oklahoma.

07:55.075 --> 07:56.910
[BELLOWING]

07:58.445 --> 08:00.147
You may be as pretty
as my sister,

08:00.147 --> 08:01.348
but don't ride like her.

08:01.348 --> 08:03.984
TUFF:
This bull's prettier
than your sister.

08:07.087 --> 08:09.022
Okay, boys. Okay, boys.

08:10.858 --> 08:12.660
[BULL BELLOWING,
AUDIENCE CHEERING]

08:14.461 --> 08:16.630
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

08:22.970 --> 08:23.971
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

08:25.573 --> 08:29.176
ANNOUNCER:
Eight seconds. Lane Frost
from Lane, Oklahoma.

08:29.176 --> 08:30.778
He's just lucky.

08:30.778 --> 08:33.145
You get a good bull, that's half
your score right there.

08:33.145 --> 08:35.549
Yeah, well, he stays on
and makes a good ride.

08:35.549 --> 08:37.384
That's the other half.

08:37.384 --> 08:38.586
ANNOUNCER:
Eighty-three.

08:38.586 --> 08:39.986
Good enough to win second.

08:39.986 --> 08:42.222
Just listen to those people
out there...

08:42.222 --> 08:45.893
TUFF:
Hey. Hey, lucky boy.

08:45.893 --> 08:48.061
Your shirt ain't
pretty no more.

08:49.730 --> 08:51.665
You got a little mud
on your feather there.

08:55.335 --> 08:57.671
All right, make sure
you get that over real good.

08:57.671 --> 08:59.272
He's gonna come
blowing out of there hard.

08:59.272 --> 09:01.675
No, he don't. He's gonna
come out and start spinning

09:01.675 --> 09:03.510
flatter than a pancake.
He's gonna blow.

09:03.510 --> 09:06.046
He's gonna spin.

09:06.046 --> 09:08.415
Blow.
Spin.

09:08.415 --> 09:10.984
Shut up
and pull my damn rope, man.

09:10.984 --> 09:13.887
CODY:
Make some money, all right?

09:13.887 --> 09:14.822
LANE:
He's gonna blow.

09:14.822 --> 09:17.157
He's gonna spin.

09:17.157 --> 09:18.892
Blow.
Spin.

09:18.892 --> 09:20.127
He's gonna blow.

09:20.127 --> 09:21.762
He's gonna spin.

09:21.762 --> 09:25.866
ANNOUNCER:
...stay on this bull's back
for eight seconds.

09:25.866 --> 09:27.067
Let's go, boys.

09:30.170 --> 09:33.206
ANNOUNCER:
Oh, boy, look at that
bull blow out of there.

09:33.206 --> 09:36.209
[SPITS]

09:36.209 --> 09:40.881
ANNOUNCER:
Well, goodbye $65 entry fee.
I'd pay him off anyway.

09:40.881 --> 09:42.750
That was a fine little try.

09:42.750 --> 09:44.584
No score, no money
for Tuff Hedeman.

09:47.921 --> 09:50.090
Hedeman seems very upset
about that right over there.

09:50.090 --> 09:51.692
There's a piece
Of little finger

09:51.692 --> 09:53.393
On a fence out in Cheyenne,

09:53.393 --> 09:57.197
They had a wild horse race,
I thought I'd lend a hand.

09:57.197 --> 09:59.967
I left bone chips
Down in Tucson

09:59.967 --> 10:01.935
With a doctor and a nurse,

10:01.935 --> 10:04.705
And gave blood in Oklahoma
Just to help me reimburse.

10:04.705 --> 10:07.975
In Omaha, Nebraska
I left a chunk of chin.

10:07.975 --> 10:09.843
I tried to find it later,

10:09.843 --> 10:12.780
But forgot
Where all I'd been.

10:12.780 --> 10:15.082
MAN 1: Good Jesus.
There you go.

10:16.516 --> 10:18.652
All I'm saying is you could've
been in the money,

10:18.652 --> 10:21.755
instead of in the mud. I told
you he blows out of there, Tuff.

10:21.755 --> 10:23.891
Yeah, well, if you had
any sense at all, pretty boy,

10:23.891 --> 10:25.959
you'd know he was thinking
about spinning

10:25.959 --> 10:27.695
and just changed his mind
is all.

10:27.695 --> 10:30.063
Yeah, well, I'm glad
one of you is thinking.

10:30.063 --> 10:31.999
[BOTH LAUGH]

10:35.035 --> 10:37.237
You know, I don't mean
to tell a feller his business,

10:37.237 --> 10:40.107
especially about bulls, but you
gotta keep bending your arm.

10:40.107 --> 10:41.208
Like this?

10:41.208 --> 10:43.010
Yeah, kind of like that.
What's your name?

10:43.010 --> 10:44.778
Travis.
You gonna be a bull rider?

10:44.778 --> 10:46.079
Yes, sir.

10:46.079 --> 10:47.948
LANE:
Three things
you gotta keep in mind.

10:47.948 --> 10:50.250
First one is,
step on that rope.

10:50.250 --> 10:52.019
Yeah, very good.
Now, second thing.

10:52.019 --> 10:54.421
Keep your arm real high, always
reach out for the front there.

10:54.421 --> 10:55.723
Towards his head, kind of?

10:55.723 --> 10:57.457
Kind of. You don't wanna get
behind here.

10:57.457 --> 10:58.792
Pretend there's a wall there.

10:58.792 --> 11:00.460
That's the bull's territory
back here,

11:00.460 --> 11:01.929
you don't wanna be back here.

11:01.929 --> 11:02.930
Now, third thing?

11:02.930 --> 11:04.297
Umm...
Hold on with my feet?

11:04.297 --> 11:05.999
That's right. Get a good hold
with your feet.

11:05.999 --> 11:08.836
Now, bend your legs a little
bit, turn your toes out,

11:08.836 --> 11:11.104
get a hold with them feet,
chest up, arm out,

11:11.104 --> 11:13.506
you can cover him real fine.
Let's see it.

11:13.506 --> 11:16.176
All right, that's good.
Hey, oh, Travis, listen.

11:16.176 --> 11:18.011
You take care of yourself,
I gotta go now.

11:18.011 --> 11:19.579
Thanks.
I appreciate it.

11:19.579 --> 11:21.348
Congratulations,
Kellie.

11:21.348 --> 11:22.950
Thanks.

11:22.950 --> 11:25.018
You don't remember me,
do you?

11:25.018 --> 11:26.887
Lane Frost, we met
at the high school finals

11:26.887 --> 11:27.955
a couple years back.

11:27.955 --> 11:29.823
Uh, sure, Lane,
how you doing?

11:29.823 --> 11:31.391
Oh, I'm all right.

11:31.391 --> 11:33.761
I don't usually watch barrel
racing, I liked watching you.

11:33.761 --> 11:35.763
You make it look
real interesting.

11:35.763 --> 11:36.997
[LAUGHS]

11:36.997 --> 11:38.766
Well, my horse Crawford
does all the work.

11:38.766 --> 11:42.269
Yeah. What do you think maybe
about getting us a bite to eat,

11:42.269 --> 11:43.871
something real quick?

11:43.871 --> 11:45.939
Oh, I'm with my mom.

11:45.939 --> 11:48.008
Well,
your mom's gotta eat, too.

11:48.008 --> 11:50.844
Uh, this is my mom,
Carolyn Kyle.

11:50.844 --> 11:51.912
This is Lane Frost.

11:51.912 --> 11:53.113
Well, Miss Carolyn,

11:53.113 --> 11:54.447
it is certainly
a pleasure to meet you.

11:54.447 --> 11:56.850
That was quite a ride today.
Oh, thank you.

11:56.850 --> 11:59.119
Did you watch him, honey?
Mm-mm.

11:59.119 --> 12:00.821
Kellie doesn't like
bull riding much.

12:00.821 --> 12:03.190
Well, it's a little rough,
you know.

12:03.190 --> 12:05.092
Um, we were fixing
to get us a bite to eat,

12:05.092 --> 12:07.260
and I would appreciate it
if you could join us.

12:07.260 --> 12:08.061
TUFF:
Lane.

12:08.061 --> 12:09.596
Let's go, butt hole.

12:09.596 --> 12:12.632
Well, I guess
I got to go.

12:12.632 --> 12:13.700
Where you all up next?

12:13.700 --> 12:15.068
Nacogdoches,
next weekend.

12:15.068 --> 12:17.137
Heck, I'm up at Nacogdoches
next weekend.

12:17.137 --> 12:19.039
What do you say we just grab
that bite to eat there?

12:19.039 --> 12:20.941
That sounds good,
doesn't it, honey?

12:20.941 --> 12:22.009
Sure.
All right.

12:22.009 --> 12:24.377
Well, you all take care.

12:24.377 --> 12:25.578
Bye.

12:25.578 --> 12:27.147
Bye-bye.

12:27.147 --> 12:28.381
Bye.

12:31.118 --> 12:32.719
KELLIE:
I don't like bull riders.

12:32.719 --> 12:34.187
Little men with big egos.

12:34.187 --> 12:36.023
Lane seems
kind of different.

12:36.023 --> 12:39.392
KELLIE:
He's got one of those skinny
butts like the rest of 'em.

12:39.392 --> 12:40.693
Honey, I judge a man more

12:40.693 --> 12:42.095
by the size of his heart
than his rear.

12:42.095 --> 12:45.365
It's likely to do you
more good.

12:45.365 --> 12:47.234
Come on, Crawford.

12:47.234 --> 12:49.069
[***]

12:51.038 --> 12:53.606
CODY:
Hey, Tuff, how are you gonna
cover your entry fee

12:53.606 --> 12:55.142
in San Angelo?
TUFF: Shut up, Cody.

12:55.142 --> 12:56.343
LANE:
I can cover you.

12:56.343 --> 12:58.078
TUFF:
I don't want your money, Lane.

12:58.078 --> 13:00.447
LANE:
Well, I got the prize money,
wood-chopping money...

13:00.447 --> 13:03.050
TUFF:
All right, all right.
I'll pay you back when I win.

13:03.050 --> 13:04.717
LANE:
I guess I can
hold out that long.

13:04.717 --> 13:06.219
[CODY LAUGHS]

13:06.219 --> 13:08.822
TUFF:
Hey. I make the jokes
in this family, all right?

13:08.822 --> 13:10.958
[***]

13:14.127 --> 13:18.065
Oh, darling, now, that does
sound tempting, but...

13:18.065 --> 13:20.367
It just won't come off.

13:24.237 --> 13:27.240
Well, I-I did pretty good
in Helotes, I got second.

13:27.240 --> 13:29.109
Ask him when
he's coming home.

13:29.109 --> 13:31.011
LANE:
Hey, I won $500, though.

13:31.011 --> 13:32.245
Well, with a little
more try,

13:32.245 --> 13:35.448
you could have won a thousand.

13:35.448 --> 13:37.150
Yeah, you're right.

13:37.150 --> 13:39.252
Then who-- Who do you think's
had the most wrecks?

13:39.252 --> 13:41.321
Charlie Samson, Cletus,
you know that.

13:41.321 --> 13:44.424
Busted his ankle, his wrist,
his sternum and his leg.

13:44.424 --> 13:45.658
He punctured his lung.

13:45.658 --> 13:46.726
Who you talking about?

13:46.726 --> 13:48.261
Charlie Samson.

13:48.261 --> 13:50.230
Oh, I'll tell you what,
I've seen him bust his head

13:50.230 --> 13:52.199
a time or two, and got his ear
ripped clean off.

13:52.199 --> 13:53.901
At least he never did
break his nose.

13:53.901 --> 13:55.402
I wonder why that is.

13:55.402 --> 13:56.469
Just lucky, I reckon.

13:56.469 --> 13:58.305
[LAUGHS]

13:58.305 --> 14:00.207
MAN:
Hey.

14:00.207 --> 14:03.710
You boys kicked ass today.
I'm gonna buy you all a drink.

14:03.710 --> 14:04.912
Well, you're
a gentleman.

14:04.912 --> 14:06.279
Yeah.
Heck, I'll have a Coke.

14:06.279 --> 14:08.148
I ain't buying nobody
no Coke.

14:08.148 --> 14:10.217
That's all right,
I don't want anything.

14:10.217 --> 14:12.152
Come on, I said
I'm buying you a drink.

14:12.152 --> 14:14.521
Buy him what he wants,
fat boy, all right?

14:14.521 --> 14:16.323
I don't give a shit
what he wants.

14:16.323 --> 14:17.124
Hey, hold it.

14:17.124 --> 14:19.259
[SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

14:21.428 --> 14:22.762
Hey--Come on, now.

14:22.762 --> 14:24.164
You said a bronc rider,
ain't you?

14:24.164 --> 14:25.265
Yeah, that's right.

14:25.265 --> 14:26.466
Well, what's your name?

14:26.466 --> 14:28.301
TUFF:
Shithead.

14:28.301 --> 14:30.737
John.
John, that's a great name.

14:30.737 --> 14:33.273
TUFF: Fat boy.
Good to meet you.

14:33.273 --> 14:36.609
What the hell's Lane doing?

14:36.609 --> 14:37.844
Running for mayor?

14:37.844 --> 14:39.346
He's probably running
for dog catcher.

14:39.346 --> 14:41.348
Let's shoot
a game of pool.

14:43.917 --> 14:46.519
So when did your daddy
quit rodeoing?

14:46.519 --> 14:48.321
Oh, I guess about 1968.

14:48.321 --> 14:50.490
Decided he was gonna stay home,
take care of the ranch.

14:50.490 --> 14:53.426
Of course, before that, top 15
cowboys, year in and year out.

14:53.426 --> 14:56.296
MAN:
Hey! I told you,
I'm dancing with her, all right?

14:56.296 --> 14:59.899
Get your hands off my girl.

14:59.899 --> 15:01.834
[WOMEN SCREAMING]

15:01.834 --> 15:03.836
Hey, hey, hey!

15:03.836 --> 15:05.973
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

15:09.943 --> 15:12.479
MAN:
Outside. Let's go.

15:12.479 --> 15:13.280
[TUFF LAUGHS]

15:13.280 --> 15:15.248
[ALL SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

15:15.248 --> 15:18.285
Get him in the car,
Lane.

15:18.285 --> 15:20.587
You try getting him in the car.

15:20.587 --> 15:24.424
TUFF:
Oh, shit, Lane,
I gotta take a piss.

15:24.424 --> 15:25.758
[TIRES SCREECHING]

15:25.758 --> 15:27.694
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING]

15:35.202 --> 15:39.906
You didn't even have
a drink tonight, did you, Lane?

15:39.906 --> 15:43.710
You didn't even have a beer.

15:43.710 --> 15:46.279
I don't drink a whole lot.

15:46.279 --> 15:48.982
You can't be a cowboy
and a nice guy, Lane.

15:48.982 --> 15:51.018
It just don't
work like that.

15:51.018 --> 15:53.020
