to uphold.

15:53.020 --> 15:55.388
Drinkin', lovin',
fightin' cowboys.

15:55.388 --> 15:58.158
Hey, Lane.
Tuff thinks he's John Wayne.

15:59.259 --> 16:01.128
You're damn right.

16:01.128 --> 16:03.630
We're a tradition.

16:03.630 --> 16:05.332
Last of a dying breed.

16:05.332 --> 16:09.302
Yeah, well, maybe there's
a reason for that dying part.

16:09.302 --> 16:13.040
Shit. These two-bit rodeos
don't mean nothing.

16:13.040 --> 16:14.774
You win a couple hundred
here and there.

16:14.774 --> 16:16.376
It's all bullshit.

16:16.376 --> 16:20.413
Cheyenne, Houston, Del Rio,
that's where the big money is.

16:20.413 --> 16:22.415
And that's where the real
cowboys are gonna be.

16:22.415 --> 16:24.317
Let me tell you
something else, pretty boy.

16:24.317 --> 16:27.554
That's where you're gonna get
your skinny ass kicked.

16:29.456 --> 16:31.424
How come?

16:31.424 --> 16:34.127
'Cause you ain't got
what it takes.

16:34.127 --> 16:36.996
You ain't goddamn
good enough.

16:36.996 --> 16:38.798
You're a puss.

16:38.798 --> 16:40.833
[LAUGHS]

16:40.833 --> 16:43.403
You dream about that.

16:45.105 --> 16:46.573
[BELCHES]

16:59.386 --> 17:02.989
When Tuff's being mean
and hateful like that,

17:02.989 --> 17:05.492
your best bet's
just to ignore him.

17:06.659 --> 17:08.494
[SIGHS]

17:08.494 --> 17:12.432
He's going to be his normal,
sweet self in the morning.

17:20.807 --> 17:23.109
Lord, I love this.

17:24.577 --> 17:28.115
[DEEP RUMBLE]

17:41.961 --> 17:44.097
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

18:02.715 --> 18:05.718
[GROANING]

18:05.718 --> 18:07.787
You wet the bed.

18:11.491 --> 18:14.894
LANE:
Urine ain't something to be
played with like that.

18:14.894 --> 18:18.431
You can't ride a bull
with no diaper rash.

18:18.431 --> 18:22.369
Cody, how do you put up with him
peeing in the bed all the time?

18:22.369 --> 18:25.138
CODY:
Well, you get used to it.

18:25.138 --> 18:28.074
LANE:
I don't wanna get used to it.

18:28.074 --> 18:29.409
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

18:29.409 --> 18:31.544
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

18:41.688 --> 18:42.789
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

18:45.758 --> 18:48.428
[***]

18:48.428 --> 18:49.962
Nice ridin' today, Lane.

18:49.962 --> 18:51.664
Thank you. I appreciate it.

18:51.664 --> 18:53.132
You betcha.

18:57.670 --> 18:59.539
Hi, Kellie.

18:59.539 --> 19:01.208
Hi.

19:01.208 --> 19:03.776
So we're gonna go get
something to eat?

19:03.776 --> 19:05.178
What?

19:05.178 --> 19:06.579
Remember, in Amarillo,
we said

19:06.579 --> 19:08.415
we were gonna get us
a bite to eat?

19:08.415 --> 19:13.019
I have to go. I'm sorry.
I made some other plans.

19:13.019 --> 19:14.754
Well...

19:14.754 --> 19:17.390
Heck, I've been planning this
for a whole week.

19:17.390 --> 19:20.092
Uh...
I'm really sorry.

19:20.092 --> 19:23.530
Your mom could come with us
if you want.

19:24.764 --> 19:26.466
Well...

19:31.471 --> 19:33.039
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING]

19:33.039 --> 19:34.741
KELLIE:
I don't rodeo full-time.

19:34.741 --> 19:36.743
I'm in college.

19:36.743 --> 19:38.445
For what?

19:38.445 --> 19:41.481
It's a sports
medicine program.

19:41.481 --> 19:44.317
I love helping people
and I love rodeo,

19:44.317 --> 19:48.355
so it's a way
to put 'em both together.

19:48.355 --> 19:50.089
I got so many plans.

19:50.089 --> 19:53.426
I don't know how I'm gonna
get 'em all done.

19:53.426 --> 19:56.429
Them plans include
riding a bull?

19:57.797 --> 19:59.899
Not hardly.

19:59.899 --> 20:02.702
Don't you ever worry
about getting injured?

20:02.702 --> 20:03.670
Mm-hm. No.

20:03.670 --> 20:05.405
I'm holding together
a lot better

20:05.405 --> 20:07.039
than a lot of them
thought I would.

20:07.039 --> 20:09.809
Well, they say it's not
if you get hurt riding bulls,

20:09.809 --> 20:11.110
it's how bad.

20:11.110 --> 20:13.280
Aw, heck, them bulls ain't
got nothing against you.

20:13.280 --> 20:16.249
They just want to buck you off
and get on with their business.

20:16.249 --> 20:18.718
People hurt you
a lot sooner.

20:20.253 --> 20:21.788
What do you mean?

20:23.656 --> 20:26.626
Nothing. It don't matter.

20:28.561 --> 20:33.833
I saw you talking to that kid
last week at the rodeo.

20:33.833 --> 20:35.835
Nobody else does that.

20:37.870 --> 20:40.907
Well, I remember
when I was a little kid,

20:40.907 --> 20:44.944
my dad took me to this rodeo
up in Utah, you know, and, uh,

20:44.944 --> 20:47.880
it was the first time I got to
sneak back behind the chutes

20:47.880 --> 20:49.316
and see all them cowboys.

20:49.316 --> 20:51.351
And I got back there

20:51.351 --> 20:54.086
and they didn't want
nothing to do with me.

20:54.086 --> 20:56.423
So I said right then and there,
"If I ever get here,

20:56.423 --> 20:58.558
I'm gonna talk
to everybody," you know?

20:58.558 --> 21:00.760
Them little kids
that come back there,

21:00.760 --> 21:03.596
they need somebody to look
up to. I looked up to my dad.

21:03.596 --> 21:04.964
Some kids,
they don't got that,

21:04.964 --> 21:06.899
so I figure if I can
be there for them, well,

21:06.899 --> 21:08.901
that's just part
of the job, you know.

21:08.901 --> 21:11.538
Rodeo is not just about women
and making money,

21:11.538 --> 21:13.373
it's about--
it's about being your best

21:13.373 --> 21:16.409
and helping others to be
their best, too, you know?

21:16.409 --> 21:19.111
I guess it's something I dreamed
about ever since I was a kid

21:19.111 --> 21:21.013
and now I'm living a dream.

21:22.982 --> 21:24.551
How's your chicken?

21:25.785 --> 21:28.220
Oh, oh.

21:28.220 --> 21:30.256
It's fine.

21:30.256 --> 21:31.891
Good.

21:35.194 --> 21:37.296
KELLIE:
Barrel racing's more
than just riding.

21:37.296 --> 21:40.467
When I'm running Crawford,
it's like I'm part of him.

21:40.467 --> 21:42.602
I gotta give him
all my trust.

21:42.602 --> 21:44.704
Well, heck, bull riding
ain't all that different.

21:44.704 --> 21:46.573
I mean, I got a lot of respect
for them bulls.

21:46.573 --> 21:48.375
When one of them comes
busting out of that gate,

21:48.375 --> 21:51.711
it's like--it's like you're
tied onto a tornado, you know,

21:51.711 --> 21:54.981
and all the energy just jumping;
not trying to break his spirit,

21:54.981 --> 21:57.316
you're just trying to stay
with him, jump for jump.

21:57.316 --> 22:00.587
It's like every wild
or free thing in the world's

22:00.587 --> 22:03.523
right there in the palm
of your hand, you know?

22:03.523 --> 22:05.558
Probably sounds
pretty stupid to you.

22:05.558 --> 22:08.961
No.
No, it's not stupid.

22:08.961 --> 22:10.997
I know what you mean.

22:14.701 --> 22:16.936
I'm real glad
you remembered about dinner.

22:16.936 --> 22:20.006
Well, I wouldn't forget
something like that.

22:24.343 --> 22:27.113
I'm riding in Lubbock
next weekend.

22:27.113 --> 22:31.283
We're up in Lubbock.

22:31.283 --> 22:32.885
I guess
we'll see you there.

22:32.885 --> 22:34.887
Yeah, I hope so.

22:40.192 --> 22:42.629
Thanks for dinner.

22:42.629 --> 22:44.196
Oh.

22:44.196 --> 22:46.799
No, that was
my pleasure, really.

22:50.970 --> 22:53.005
Well...

22:57.009 --> 22:59.078
Night, Lane.

23:00.780 --> 23:02.449
Night.

23:14.226 --> 23:15.795
Night.

23:16.963 --> 23:18.865
Good night.

23:24.471 --> 23:25.905
[SIGHS]

23:27.306 --> 23:29.075
[***]

23:29.075 --> 23:32.011
CODY:
Lane, you've been seeing a lot
of Kellie the last few months.

23:32.011 --> 23:34.581
LANE:
You know, she was real upset
last time you all got together.

23:34.581 --> 23:37.750
TUFF:
What are you talking about?
I heard you stayed on 8 seconds

23:37.750 --> 23:40.086
and jumped off
and threw your hat in the air.

23:40.086 --> 23:41.754
[ALL LAUGH]

23:57.770 --> 23:59.171
LANE:
I'll just be a minute.

23:59.171 --> 24:00.840
CODY:
You better hope
Tuff doesn't wake up

24:00.840 --> 24:03.009
and find out we're in Texas.

24:07.313 --> 24:09.949
Lane. Hi.

24:09.949 --> 24:11.017
We, uh...

24:11.017 --> 24:12.819
We're just passing through,
you know.

24:12.819 --> 24:15.321
I thought I'd stop by.

24:15.321 --> 24:18.758
Oh. I'm glad you did.

24:18.758 --> 24:20.092
Good.

24:21.694 --> 24:24.263
[***]

24:24.263 --> 24:26.999
Where'd y'all come from?

24:26.999 --> 24:29.536
California.

24:29.536 --> 24:31.037
Where are you headed?

24:31.037 --> 24:34.206
Oh, we're going
to Nebraska.

24:34.206 --> 24:38.878
Lane, Texas isn't on the way
from California to Nebraska.

24:38.878 --> 24:40.179
Oh.

24:40.179 --> 24:41.681
Well...

24:41.681 --> 24:45.585
I never did have much of
a sense of direction, you know.

24:45.585 --> 24:48.087
You got real pretty land
here, Kellie.

24:48.087 --> 24:50.690
Thanks.

24:50.690 --> 24:53.926
Sure would like to have me
some like it someday.

24:53.926 --> 24:57.564
Of course, I just grew up
on a little ranch, you know.

24:57.564 --> 25:00.199
Lane, that doesn't
matter to me.

25:01.934 --> 25:04.571
We're just
country people.

25:06.338 --> 25:08.507
Country people
are the best kind.

25:08.507 --> 25:11.210
Hard-working,
down to earth,

25:11.210 --> 25:13.713
sincere.

25:13.713 --> 25:16.783
How about if we ride bulls?

25:16.783 --> 25:20.252
I guess everybody's
a little peculiar.

25:23.522 --> 25:25.892
TUFF:
Ah, where are we now?

25:25.892 --> 25:29.929
Quanah, Texas.
Home of Kellie Kyle.

25:31.731 --> 25:33.165
What did you say?

25:33.165 --> 25:35.267
You heard me.

25:37.737 --> 25:40.673
There are girls
all over the rodeo,

25:40.673 --> 25:42.174
isn't that right,
Cletus?

25:42.174 --> 25:43.843
Yeah, there are.

25:43.843 --> 25:48.380
Why in the hell do we have
to detour 500 miles

25:48.380 --> 25:49.916
just for this one?

25:49.916 --> 25:52.785
Love knows
no boundaries.

25:54.353 --> 25:58.524
A puss in love.

25:58.524 --> 26:00.159
It's pitiful.

26:02.595 --> 26:04.030
You know, Kellie,

26:04.030 --> 26:06.432
Del Rio's the first real
big bull ride of the year.

26:06.432 --> 26:09.301
I'd be plumb tickled
if you'd come watch me.

26:09.301 --> 26:11.137
I'd love to, Lane,

26:11.137 --> 26:12.772
but I got finals.

26:12.772 --> 26:14.573
Aw, heck,
that ain't no problem.

26:14.573 --> 26:16.976
Just study during
all them other events

26:16.976 --> 26:18.377
and look up
when I come on.

26:18.377 --> 26:19.946
[LAUGHS SOFTLY]

26:19.946 --> 26:22.581
I'll think about it.

26:23.582 --> 26:25.952
I expect I'd best go.

26:25.952 --> 26:27.386
Y'all wanna stay
for supper?

26:27.386 --> 26:29.021
We got plenty.

26:29.021 --> 26:33.960
No, I--
We really should go.

26:33.960 --> 26:35.662
Thanks for stopping by.

26:35.662 --> 26:38.230
Well, you got
a heck of a place here.

26:38.230 --> 26:39.999
Yes, sir.

26:39.999 --> 26:42.635
Be about perfect
for the wedding.

26:42.635 --> 26:44.436
What wedding?

26:44.436 --> 26:47.907
Yours and mine.

26:47.907 --> 26:50.877
Ah. I'm glad
you told me.

26:50.877 --> 26:54.213
I'll try to keep
the day open.

26:58.117 --> 26:59.752
Lane,

26:59.752 --> 27:02.922
you never even
kiss me.

27:02.922 --> 27:04.023
Oh.

27:04.023 --> 27:06.859
Well, what do you expect
from an Okie

27:06.859 --> 27:09.428
who can't get from
California to Nebraska?

27:09.428 --> 27:10.997
Heh.

27:14.734 --> 27:17.236
I don't chew tobacco
or nothing.

27:21.373 --> 27:24.911
TUFF:
Oh, Kellie. Ooh. Whoo!

27:24.911 --> 27:27.046
[TUFF AND CODY LAUGH]

27:30.516 --> 27:32.651
[***]

27:51.470 --> 27:53.405
[INDISTINCT SPEECH]

28:17.830 --> 28:21.934
ANNOUNCER:
Check this out,
a rider from Tulsa, Oklahoma.

28:21.934 --> 28:23.669
Stay with him.

28:23.669 --> 28:26.705
He's got a good seat and
looks like he's gonna make it.

28:26.705 --> 28:29.675
He did!

28:29.675 --> 28:32.644
This is it, boys.
Big time, big money.

28:32.644 --> 28:34.013
Yep.

28:35.147 --> 28:37.083
ANNOUNCER:
Seventy-nine points.

28:37.083 --> 28:39.385
Tuff, look over there,
it's Gary Leffew, man,

28:39.385 --> 28:40.987
it's Gary Leffew!
I can't believe

28:40.987 --> 28:43.022
we're in the same bull ride
as a world champ.

28:43.022 --> 28:45.357
That's what they'll be
saying about us someday.

28:45.357 --> 28:46.993
Ain't that Lane Frost?

28:46.993 --> 28:48.895
And look over there,
there's Tuff Hedeman.

28:48.895 --> 28:51.764
I did not know he was
such a handsome son of a gun.

28:51.764 --> 28:53.732
[BOTH LAUGH]

28:54.834 --> 28:56.803
Did you see that, Cody?
Uh-huh.

28:56.803 --> 28:57.937
He actually got a joke.

28:57.937 --> 29:00.106
Lane Frost
has a sense of humor.

29:00.106 --> 29:03.142
He ain't as dumb
as I thought.

29:03.142 --> 29:05.077
I can't be that
dumb, boys.

29:05.077 --> 29:06.412
I'm doing what I love.

29:06.412 --> 29:07.713
Look, there's Red Rock.

29:07.713 --> 29:09.849
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

29:14.120 --> 29:15.955
That only lasted
about four seconds.

29:15.955 --> 29:17.289
I'll tell you what,
man,

29:17.289 --> 29:19.091
I'd give anything
for a chance at Red Rock.

29:19.091 --> 29:20.626
You should
forget about him.

29:20.626 --> 29:23.362
Start thinking about
Savage Seven, 'cause you're up.

29:23.362 --> 29:25.297
[CHUTE OPENS]

29:27.166 --> 29:29.836
ANNOUNCER:
Lane Frost
from Lane, Oklahoma.

29:29.836 --> 29:32.404
Okay, boys. Okay, boys.

29:32.404 --> 29:34.040
[CROWD CHEERING]

29:34.040 --> 29:36.008
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

29:48.054 --> 29:50.789
ANNOUNCER:
No score for Lane Frost.

29:50.789 --> 29:52.591
[MOANING]

29:52.591 --> 29:55.127
Lane's gonna have to have
a magnificent ride tomorrow

29:55.127 --> 29:56.996
to be eligible for
some of that prize money.

29:56.996 --> 29:58.730
CODY:
Take it easy.

29:58.730 --> 29:59.731
[GROANS]

29:59.731 --> 30:01.333
Lay back.

30:03.870 --> 30:05.972
It's okay,
I'm with Lane.

30:05.972 --> 30:07.573
I'm sorry, you can't
go in there right now.

30:07.573 --> 30:10.309
Please, I gotta go in there.
You'll have to wait outside.

30:16.548 --> 30:19.685
Oh. Is my dick still there?

30:19.685 --> 30:21.620
It's hanging
by a thread.

30:21.620 --> 30:22.621
No, no, no.

30:22.621 --> 30:24.523
You don't
wanna see it.

30:24.523 --> 30:26.192
Cody, is he all right?

30:26.192 --> 30:28.127
He's gonna be fine, now,
he's gonna be fine.

30:28.127 --> 30:29.261
He just won't be...

30:29.261 --> 30:31.263
such a romantic buckaroo
for a while,

30:31.263 --> 30:33.399
but he's gonna be fine.

30:36.302 --> 30:38.437
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
IN DISTANCE]

30:40.106 --> 30:42.942
You don't have
to baby-sit me.

30:42.942 --> 30:44.911
I think I'm gonna
stick around.

30:44.911 --> 30:48.347
See how far them balls
swell up, see if they pop.

30:48.347 --> 30:49.548
[SIGHS]

30:49.548 --> 30:54.620
Biggest money ride so far
this year, and I fall off.

30:54.620 --> 30:56.522
Maybe my dad's right.

30:56.522 --> 30:57.456
I could rodeo my whole life,

30:57.456 --> 31:00.692
end up worse off
than when I started.

31:00.692 --> 31:02.594
You could.

31:02.594 --> 31:04.997
I seen old cowboys.

31:04.997 --> 31:06.465
Rodeo beat 'em up so bad

31:06.465 --> 31:09.801
they can't hardly get out
the bed come the morning.

31:09.801 --> 31:11.637
I don't want that.

31:12.972 --> 31:17.109
Well, maybe you ought
to just quit, Lane.

31:17.109 --> 31:19.578
Go home,
work your daddy's ranch,

31:19.578 --> 31:22.281
live to be a hundred.

31:22.281 --> 31:26.885
Sit in your rocking chair,
watch the sun go down.

31:26.885 --> 31:28.921
That'd be nice,
wouldn't it?

31:28.921 --> 31:30.622
Real special.

31:30.622 --> 31:33.926
Did you hear me say
anything about quitting?

31:35.761 --> 31:39.498
And just before you croak...

31:39.498 --> 31:42.401
one last little thought's
gonna keep going

31:42.401 --> 31:44.470
through that pretty
little head of yours

31:44.470 --> 31:47.839
over and over again:

31:47.839 --> 31:50.142
"I'm a puss."

31:50.142 --> 31:53.612
"I was the best goddamned
bull rider in the circuit

31:53.612 --> 31:54.680
and I chickened out."

31:54.680 --> 31:56.115
Hell, the best?

31:56.115 --> 31:57.749
All you ever tell me
is how I ain't no good.

31:57.749 --> 32:00.252
Well, if you believe everything
you hear, goddamn it,

32:00.252 --> 32:02.688
you're dumber
than I thought, Lane!

32:03.922 --> 32:05.624
Quit.

32:05.624 --> 32:08.260
That'd be fine with me.

32:08.260 --> 32:10.529
I wouldn't have to wake up
every goddamned morning

32:10.529 --> 32:11.763
to your pretty-boy face.

32:11.763 --> 32:13.732
Me and Cody'd get down
the road a lot faster, too,

32:13.732 --> 32:15.801
if we didn't have to stand
around waiting for you

32:15.801 --> 32:18.270
signing autographs
for every snot-nosed little kid

32:18.270 --> 32:20.872
at every goddamned rodeo!
All right, all right.

32:20.872 --> 32:23.709
I got two words
to say to you:

32:23.709 --> 32:24.810
Yeah, I know--

32:24.810 --> 32:28.047
That ain't it.

32:28.047 --> 32:30.882
Well, what is it?

32:30.882 --> 32:33.085
Cowboy up.

32:36.755 --> 32:38.757
Hey.

32:38.757 --> 32:40.659
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
IN DISTANCE]

32:50.969 --> 32:52.604
Puss.

32:52.604 --> 32:56.542
ANNOUNCER:
Let's pick up the action
with Lane Frost.

32:56.542 --> 32:58.744
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

32:58.744 --> 32:59.945
TUFF:
Mind your business.

32:59.945 --> 33:02.948
You got the guts,
now comes the glory.

33:02.948 --> 33:04.916
Go, Lane!

33:04.916 --> 33:07.919
ANNOUNCER:
Here's Lane Frost,
on the bull, the bull

33:07.919 --> 33:10.289
they call Double Trouble.

33:10.289 --> 33:12.458
Okay, boys, okay, boys!

33:12.458 --> 33:13.725
[***]

33:23.069 --> 33:25.071
Lane, come on!

33:25.071 --> 33:26.672
Oh, yeah!

33:26.672 --> 33:28.240
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

33:33.812 --> 33:35.414
[SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

33:37.516 --> 33:38.950
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

33:38.950 --> 33:41.053
See that? Way to go, Lane!

33:43.755 --> 33:47.426
ANNOUNCER:
A textbook ride
by the Oklahoma cowboy.

33:47.426 --> 33:51.463
One of our judges got
a 45 marking on one side.

33:51.463 --> 33:54.032
Forty-five on the other.

33:54.032 --> 33:58.137
Ninety points for Lane Frost!

33:58.137 --> 34:01.006
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

34:01.006 --> 34:04.776
ANNOUNCER:
Here's a guy the doctor
suggested stay in bed,

34:04.776 --> 34:10.047
he comes out here
and turns in a 90-point ride.

34:11.650 --> 34:14.120
LANE:
I thought he was gonna
turn right right there.

34:14.120 --> 34:15.887
CLYDE:
Don't try to second-guess
a bull.

34:15.887 --> 34:18.524
He could have throwed you
right out the back door.

34:18.524 --> 34:21.960
Look, look, your weight's
all on the wrong leg.

34:21.960 --> 34:25.697
Must have done something right.
I got second place.

34:25.697 --> 34:29.835
You're just lucky
the other boys rode so poor.

34:36.708 --> 34:39.710
ANNOUNCER [OVER TV]:
Here's a guy the doctor
suggested stay in bed,

34:39.710 --> 34:44.716
comes out here
and turns in a 90-point ride.

34:44.716 --> 34:46.284
[FLIES BUZZING]

34:53.692 --> 34:55.161
[GRUNTS]

34:58.930 --> 35:00.199
Lane?

35:00.199 --> 35:01.467
What are you
doing down here?

35:01.467 --> 35:03.935
I thought you was
up helping my mom.

35:03.935 --> 35:05.003
Lane, what's wrong?

35:05.003 --> 35:07.173
Nothing,
I'm fine.

35:08.974 --> 35:11.343
Your mom's great.

35:11.343 --> 35:13.712
I've never been brought home
to meet the folks before,

35:13.712 --> 35:16.748
but she made me feel
right at home.

35:18.049 --> 35:20.252
I haven't had a chance
to visit with your dad yet.

35:20.252 --> 35:21.887
Well, he's great.

35:21.887 --> 35:24.423
Tell you what, if I do half what
that man's done in his life,

35:24.423 --> 35:25.724
I'll be doing good.

35:25.724 --> 35:28.460
He's kept this ranch going
with no money.

35:28.460 --> 35:29.728
You got your family killing,

35:29.728 --> 35:31.563
my daddy ain't no president
of a bank.

35:31.563 --> 35:34.500
Every little thing we got
that man worked for.

35:34.500 --> 35:38.370
Gets up at 5 every morning,
doesn't stop till after dark.

35:38.370 --> 35:40.572
He can out-work me
any day of the week.

35:40.572 --> 35:42.941
Lane, you want to talk
about what's bothering you?

35:42.941 --> 35:45.511
Nothing's bothering me!

35:45.511 --> 35:48.847
I'm fine,
I told you.

35:48.847 --> 35:51.550
Okay.

35:51.550 --> 35:55.053
But if you ever need
to talk about anything...

35:55.053 --> 35:57.356
talk to me...

35:58.290 --> 35:59.691
Nothing you
could say or do

35:59.691 --> 36:02.528
would make you
less in my eyes.

36:05.597 --> 36:08.400
I love you.

36:08.400 --> 36:11.970
You don't have
to be perfect for me.

36:11.970 --> 36:14.506
You mean that?

36:14.506 --> 36:17.576
You're gonna have
to prove it.

36:17.576 --> 36:19.711
I will.

36:19.711 --> 36:23.415
Right now
I'm covered in horse shit.

36:23.415 --> 36:25.917
[***]

36:38.364 --> 36:42.868
* Love is like the wind *

36:42.868 --> 36:48.974
* Sometimes it blows your way *

36:51.410 --> 36:54.980
* And until now *

36:57.983 --> 37:00.352
* It missed me somehow *

37:00.352 --> 37:03.955
You're a great dancer.

37:03.955 --> 37:06.091
Sorry I'm so surprised.

37:06.091 --> 37:08.026
Well,
I took up the lessons

37:08.026 --> 37:10.862
'cause I knowed you was looking
forward to it.

37:10.862 --> 37:15.801
Whatever it is, Kellie,
I'll always do my best for you.

37:15.801 --> 37:19.237
I'll do my best
for you, too, Lane.

37:19.237 --> 37:23.709
If I ever mess up, you just take
an old frying pan to my head.

37:23.709 --> 37:28.714
I'll sic Red Rock on ya.
He'll take care of you.

37:31.450 --> 37:37.723
* I used to have a wish *

37:37.723 --> 37:44.696
* One day I'd feel like this *

37:44.696 --> 37:50.135
* Now I know love exists *

37:50.135 --> 37:51.470
Miss Frost.

37:51.470 --> 37:53.639
Would you care to dance?

37:53.639 --> 37:58.143
Oh. No, thank you, Cody.
But thanks for asking.

37:58.143 --> 37:59.110
It'd be my pleasure.

37:59.110 --> 38:01.413
Oh, I appreciate it.

38:01.413 --> 38:03.214
All right.

38:03.214 --> 38:04.950
[GUESTS CLAPPING]

38:04.950 --> 38:07.018
[GUITAR PLAYING]

38:14.125 --> 38:17.262
* I've been cheated *

38:17.262 --> 38:21.400
* Been mistreated *

38:21.400 --> 38:28.173
* When will I be loved? *

38:28.173 --> 38:31.443
* I've been put down *

38:31.443 --> 38:34.613
* I've been pushed 'round *

38:34.613 --> 38:39.351
* When will I be loved? *

38:41.286 --> 38:44.289
* When I find a new girl *

38:44.289 --> 38:47.158
* That I want for mine *

38:47.158 --> 38:50.862
* She always breaks
My heart in two *

38:50.862 --> 38:54.600
* It happens every time *

38:56.368 --> 38:59.638
* I've been made blue *

38:59.638 --> 39:02.808
* I've been lied to *

39:02.808 --> 39:07.112
* When will I be loved? *

39:30.936 --> 39:33.972
KELLIE:
What are you
thinking about?

39:33.972 --> 39:38.944
If Denver drew me some good
bulls that I might get a check.

39:41.046 --> 39:43.882
Maybe I should quit
school for a while.

39:43.882 --> 39:46.785
You're driving all the time.
We'll never see each other.

39:46.785 --> 39:49.588
Can always
finish up later.

39:49.588 --> 39:52.390
Whatever you want.

39:52.390 --> 39:54.760
We could rodeo together.

39:54.760 --> 39:58.797
Be together
all the time.

39:58.797 --> 40:01.099
What about Tuff and Cody?

40:01.099 --> 40:04.903
There's lots of guys
who can buddy with them.

40:07.072 --> 40:09.975
You are a prettier sight
to wake up to in the morning

40:09.975 --> 40:12.143
than Tuff Hedeman,
and that's for sure.

40:22.153 --> 40:27.158
I don't want to be away
from you for one minute.

40:27.158 --> 40:31.530
I don't know how I'm gonna be
at this husband stuff.

40:33.198 --> 40:36.301
You'll be fine.

40:36.301 --> 40:40.506
I guess it's like a bull ride.
You just get on there

40:40.506 --> 40:42.340
and hope you don't
get bucked off.

40:42.340 --> 40:44.610
Thanks a lot.

40:56.054 --> 41:00.125
[MAN SPEAKING OVER
LOUDSPEAKER INDISTINCTLY]

41:00.125 --> 41:02.828
[***]

41:12.270 --> 41:14.906
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

41:19.811 --> 41:22.581
Lane, you've won $36,000
so far in 1985.

41:22.581 --> 41:25.551
What's the biggest reason
you're competing professionally?

41:25.551 --> 41:27.653
Well, I suppose mostly,
uh, it's the money.

41:27.653 --> 41:30.421
I mean, that is how we
make our living, and....

41:30.421 --> 41:34.092
Cody and I win,
Lane gets bucked off.

41:34.092 --> 41:37.095
And they still
want to talk to him.

41:37.095 --> 41:38.496
Go figure.

41:38.496 --> 41:40.398
Buy you a beer, Tuff?

41:40.398 --> 41:44.069
Buy you one, Kel.
Come on.

41:44.069 --> 41:46.004
Well, buckers, them's
the ones we want.

41:46.004 --> 41:48.674
If there's one that can't be
rid, that's the one I want on.

41:48.674 --> 41:50.008
Y'all can stay with us
whenever you want.

41:50.008 --> 41:52.644
Just treat me
like one of the boys.

41:52.644 --> 41:54.680
You might
regret that.

41:54.680 --> 41:57.215
I've been around
rodeo my whole life.

41:57.215 --> 42:01.019
You ain't never been in a
bathroom after five bull riders.

42:01.019 --> 42:04.489
Don't worry.
I'm pretty tough.

42:04.489 --> 42:06.958
Thought I was Tuff.

42:06.958 --> 42:08.059
Two beers.

42:08.059 --> 42:09.227
I.D.?

42:09.227 --> 42:11.229
Gotcha.

42:13.965 --> 42:16.668
How'd you get
the name Tuff?

42:18.570 --> 42:20.171
When I was 4 years old,

42:20.171 --> 42:24.442
I got my hand
slammed in the car door.

42:24.442 --> 42:26.011
Never did cry or nothing.

42:26.011 --> 42:30.782
So they started calling me
Tough Enough. It got shortened.

42:30.782 --> 42:33.084
What's your real name?

42:37.388 --> 42:39.190
Richard.

42:43.929 --> 42:47.633
He's pretty special
to me, Richard.

42:47.633 --> 42:49.735
TUFF:
He does grow on you.

42:49.735 --> 42:52.203
Smiley pecker.

42:56.474 --> 42:59.911
They act like he
hung the moon.

43:06.084 --> 43:08.153
Lane.

43:09.520 --> 43:11.156
Honey?

43:14.092 --> 43:17.028
Lane.

43:17.028 --> 43:18.930
You asleep?

43:18.930 --> 43:20.699
Lane.

43:20.699 --> 43:22.000
Good morning, Kellie.

43:24.736 --> 43:27.172
Hotels was all full.

43:27.172 --> 43:30.541
Lane said it'd be okay
to bunk in with y'all.

43:30.541 --> 43:32.577
Oh.

43:32.577 --> 43:35.413
Well, how'd you sleep,
Tuff?

43:35.413 --> 43:37.115
Like an angel.

43:37.115 --> 43:38.684
Me, too.

43:39.818 --> 43:41.720
Morning, Kellie.

43:41.720 --> 43:43.154
Morning.

43:43.154 --> 43:45.323
How you doing?

43:45.323 --> 43:46.792
Great.

43:46.792 --> 43:48.794
Just great.

43:49.961 --> 43:52.030
KELLIE:
What about getting
our own place?

43:52.030 --> 43:54.565
Well, it's a good idea
if you got the money.

43:54.565 --> 43:56.134
Well, my daddy will
lend us the money.

43:56.134 --> 43:57.803
I was just talking
to him the other day.

43:57.803 --> 43:59.270
And he's got this
friend in real estate

43:59.270 --> 44:01.072
who can get us
some really good deals.

44:01.072 --> 44:04.943
Kellie, how's it gonna
be ours if he buys it?

44:04.943 --> 44:07.813
You want a place?
I'll get you a place, okay?

44:07.813 --> 44:10.548
Okay. But I want to live
near my folks

44:10.548 --> 44:12.417
since you'll
be gone so much.

44:12.417 --> 44:13.584
Wherever you want.

44:13.584 --> 44:17.288
Okay. Drive careful.

44:17.288 --> 44:18.724
[HONKING]

44:32.337 --> 44:33.471
What's that?

44:33.471 --> 44:34.873
That is exactly
what you wanted.

44:34.873 --> 44:37.442
It's a place,
close to your parents.

44:39.577 --> 44:41.479
[LAUGHING]
Uh-uh.

44:41.479 --> 44:43.214
You are just
gonna love this.

44:43.214 --> 44:46.351
I bought this off that singer,
Ray Raymond, you know?

44:46.351 --> 44:47.853
You paid money for this?

44:47.853 --> 44:49.855
Heck, I got him down
to almost nothing.

44:49.855 --> 44:51.990
It was only $600.
Can you believe that?

44:51.990 --> 44:55.994
Lane, it is the ugliest thing
I've ever seen in my life.

44:55.994 --> 44:57.628
It's got great ventilation.

44:57.628 --> 44:59.364
We're allowed to keep the TV
and all them 8-tracks can stay.

44:59.364 --> 45:02.000
I'll even get banjos
strung up if you want.

45:02.000 --> 45:05.636
Right here, Elvis Presley once
had a beer in our kitchen.

45:05.636 --> 45:06.838
Lately?

45:06.838 --> 45:08.373
No, well, I think
it was some time back,

45:08.373 --> 45:10.108
but as you can see,
it's real homey.

45:10.108 --> 45:11.676
Right here is
the bath suite,

45:11.676 --> 45:13.378
complete with
shower and curtain.

45:13.378 --> 45:15.747
Well, that was generous.

45:15.747 --> 45:17.783
Lane,
I can't live here.

45:17.783 --> 45:19.317
It'll give
me nightmares.

45:19.317 --> 45:20.585
Oh, now, honey.

45:20.585 --> 45:23.121
Couple days, you'll be
calling it home sweet home.

45:23.121 --> 45:24.489
I promise.

45:24.489 --> 45:25.757
I don't think so.

45:25.757 --> 45:28.159
Look--double closets.

45:33.698 --> 45:35.700
Hyah! Hyah! Hyah!

45:35.700 --> 45:36.935
[SCREAMS]

45:36.935 --> 45:38.236
Let's just put it
in the back, honey.

45:38.236 --> 45:40.005
No, let's put everything
up front here.

45:40.005 --> 45:41.339
That way, the ice cream
won't melt.

45:41.339 --> 45:43.408
Oh, we'll just put
the ice cream up there.

45:43.408 --> 45:45.210
Once we got it all up here,

45:45.210 --> 45:47.779
then we know where it's
at when we get home.

45:47.779 --> 45:49.180
We got more room
in the back, hon.

45:49.180 --> 45:52.450
Well, I don't know.
What's this?

45:52.450 --> 45:54.152
That is for later.

45:54.152 --> 45:55.186
Oh, you mean, it's for me.

45:55.186 --> 45:57.755
No, I mean
it's for later.

45:57.755 --> 45:59.090
Lane!

45:59.090 --> 46:01.326
Well, Kel, it ain't
my birthday or anything.

46:01.326 --> 46:04.395
No, it ain't
your birthday.

46:06.231 --> 46:08.333
Oh, it's our anniversary,
isn't it?

46:08.333 --> 46:10.301
Shoot, honey, I forgot.
Look, hold onto this--

46:10.301 --> 46:14.139
Just keep
looking in the box.

46:16.507 --> 46:18.376
Oh, Kel.

46:18.376 --> 46:19.911
Fifth in the world.

46:19.911 --> 46:22.347
It's time you started
dressing like it.

46:22.347 --> 46:24.582
You're always looking
out for me, ain't ya?

46:24.582 --> 46:27.018
Somebody's got to.

46:27.018 --> 46:28.719
I love you, honey.

46:28.719 --> 46:31.122
I love you, too.

46:33.424 --> 46:34.960
[***]

46:34.960 --> 46:37.562
I got another
surprise for you at home.

46:37.562 --> 46:40.165
Something for me to wear.

46:40.165 --> 46:42.067
Mmm.

46:42.067 --> 46:45.303
MAN [OVER LOUDSPEAKER]:
For the next 10 days, each
will ride one bull a day

46:45.303 --> 46:48.373
and the winner will
be our world's champion.

46:48.373 --> 46:51.509
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

46:58.016 --> 47:00.986
[CROWD CHEERING]

47:08.526 --> 47:09.627
[BUZZER]

47:09.627 --> 47:11.329
ANNOUNCER:
81 is what he's got to beat.

47:11.329 --> 47:12.864
He's off with the whistle!

47:14.432 --> 47:15.300
85 points!

47:15.300 --> 47:16.767
Good ride, Lane!

47:16.767 --> 47:21.406
ANNOUNCER:
85 puts him in first
place for the first round!

47:23.975 --> 47:26.945
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

47:28.146 --> 47:29.647
...This is Bull Number 8.

47:29.647 --> 47:31.616
He's trying to break
a new record here and be

47:31.616 --> 47:35.320
the first man to ride all ten
bulls at the national finals.

47:35.320 --> 47:38.556
Look at him here.
He's got no problem right now.

47:38.556 --> 47:40.491
Lane Frost...

47:41.759 --> 47:43.461
[BUZZER]

47:43.461 --> 47:46.331
ANNOUNCER:
He did it! Ladies and
gentlemen, eight in a row.

47:46.331 --> 47:48.233
Lane Frost.

47:48.233 --> 47:49.935
On the verge of a
world's championship,

47:49.935 --> 47:51.702
you've won 83,000
so far this year,

47:51.702 --> 47:54.372
you're in first place,
ahead of all 15 competitors.

47:54.372 --> 47:57.442
This first world's title's
gonna be easy, isn't it?

47:57.442 --> 48:00.878
Well, I don't think it's ever
easy, to tell you the truth,

48:00.878 --> 48:03.581
I mean, when you got bull riders
like Cody Lambert and Jim Sharp,

48:03.581 --> 48:05.616
you know, Jim's riding
real good this year,

48:05.616 --> 48:06.952
so it's gonna be tough, but,

48:06.952 --> 48:08.553
I'm just real tickled
to be here, you know?

48:08.553 --> 48:10.455
Me and my traveling
partner, Tuff Hedeman,

48:10.455 --> 48:12.257
we've been trading
places all year.

48:12.257 --> 48:15.160
Sometimes he's in first,
and next week I'm in first,

48:15.160 --> 48:16.894
and, well, I'll tell
you what. If he wins,

48:16.894 --> 48:20.231
I'd be so happy for him I'd just
forget all about myself losing.

48:20.231 --> 48:23.401
Lane Frost.
Great bull rider. Terrible liar.

48:23.401 --> 48:26.204
You're not gonna be happy
for him. Get outta here.

48:26.204 --> 48:28.439
Sure I would be.
He's luckier than I am.

48:28.439 --> 48:32.110
ANNOUNCER:
After nine days, Lane Frost
is still in first place.

48:32.110 --> 48:34.345
Now, if he gets in 86 points
or higher,

48:34.345 --> 48:39.417
nobody else can catch him
here in the competition...

48:39.417 --> 48:41.886
A lot of cowboys have had
a tough time with this bull,

48:41.886 --> 48:45.090
but look how easy Lane seems
to be handling him.

48:45.090 --> 48:47.692
I've never seen
a cowboy ride...

48:54.432 --> 48:55.533
[BUZZER]

48:55.533 --> 48:57.535
He does it!
There goes the whistle!

48:57.535 --> 48:59.237
We'll see a score
coming up for Lane--

48:59.237 --> 49:01.406
Oh, he's hung up,
ladies and gentlemen!

49:01.406 --> 49:04.042
His hand is hung up
in the rope!

49:12.183 --> 49:14.519
He's underneath the bull.

49:14.519 --> 49:17.688
Oh, Lane Frost
is underneath the bull!

49:17.688 --> 49:19.890
Bullfighters, get him off!
Ladies and gentlemen!

49:19.890 --> 49:24.095
They got him away. Lane Frost
is free from that bull!

49:24.095 --> 49:27.665
Look at that score
coming up for Lane Frost.

49:27.665 --> 49:31.069
An 87-point marking.

49:31.069 --> 49:33.938
Your new world's champion,

49:33.938 --> 49:37.575
Lane Frost, from Quanah, Texas!

49:37.575 --> 49:40.645
Lane Frost has already
won the world's championship.

49:40.645 --> 49:42.747
But he's got one
more bull to ride.

49:42.747 --> 49:46.517
If he rides that bull, he would
become the first man in history

49:46.517 --> 49:49.987
to ride all ten bulls
at the National Finals Rodeo.

49:49.987 --> 49:52.390
But he has drawn Red Rock.

49:52.390 --> 49:57.528
This bull has bucked off
over 300 cowboys.

49:57.528 --> 50:02.700
This could be a moment
that rodeo will never forget.

50:02.700 --> 50:04.169
Well, that's hard luck,

50:04.169 --> 50:06.904
you drawing Red Rock
on your last bull.

50:06.904 --> 50:08.939
Shoot. No fear
when I was drawing.

50:08.939 --> 50:12.043
We've been waiting for this
a long time, ain't we, Red Rock?

50:12.043 --> 50:14.679
Okay, boys, let's go!

50:14.679 --> 50:17.682
ANNOUNCER: Lane Frost,
world's champion bull rider,

50:17.682 --> 50:20.385
on a bull that has never been
ridden--Red Rock.

50:20.385 --> 50:23.521
Look at this! Look at the turn
this cowboy has...

50:27.024 --> 50:29.994
He could be the first cowboy
to ride all ten bulls

50:29.994 --> 50:31.796
at the National Finals Rodeo.

50:31.796 --> 50:34.499
Look at him go! Lane Frost!

50:34.499 --> 50:36.967
Whoa! He's not yet at
the 8-second whistle!

50:36.967 --> 50:40.571
That makes him Victim 305!

50:40.571 --> 50:43.341
LANE:
Shoot, I kind of think
Red Rock ought to be up here

50:43.341 --> 50:46.344
getting this award instead
of me, but since y'all went

50:46.344 --> 50:48.346
and put my name on it so nice,

50:48.346 --> 50:50.014
I guess I'll keep it.

50:50.014 --> 50:52.683
[LAUGHTER]

50:52.683 --> 50:54.452
Um...

50:55.486 --> 50:57.355
This is the biggest
dream of my life.

50:57.355 --> 50:59.624
Heck, it's the biggest
dream of any cowboy's life.

51:00.891 --> 51:02.327
Now that I'm world champ,

51:02.327 --> 51:05.963
I'm gonna do my best for all
the fans there and...

51:05.963 --> 51:08.433
Well, I just want
to thank everybody

51:08.433 --> 51:11.602
that stood behind me
on the way up.

51:11.602 --> 51:13.538
Thank you very much.

51:13.538 --> 51:14.605
[APPLAUSE]

51:14.605 --> 51:16.407
[***]

51:22.213 --> 51:27.585
* Today's the day
I'm gonna make it *

51:29.187 --> 51:30.621
Oh, these are--
These are--

51:30.621 --> 51:33.524
These are so much bigger today.
That's something.

51:33.524 --> 51:36.694
It took a lot of try
to win that, son.

51:36.694 --> 51:38.296
It's real nice.

51:38.296 --> 51:39.764
Thank you.
You know, some of them rides

51:39.764 --> 51:42.032
I felt like I was just
hanging on by a fingernail.

51:42.032 --> 51:44.469
No, no, no.
You rode real good.

51:44.469 --> 51:46.571
'Course, now the job
is staying on top.

51:46.571 --> 51:50.141
That's when we find out
if you're a real champion.

51:59.884 --> 52:01.386
Is anything wrong?

52:01.386 --> 52:02.687
Why?

52:02.687 --> 52:04.789
I just never seen you
having more than one beer.

52:04.789 --> 52:07.192
What, ain't I entitled?
Of course.

52:07.192 --> 52:08.493
I'm the world's champ now.

52:08.493 --> 52:10.561
Don't that count
for something with you?

52:10.561 --> 52:12.430
Lane.

52:15.466 --> 52:17.568
Congratulations, Lane,
you did a hell of a job.

52:17.568 --> 52:19.937
Well, thank you very much.
Appreciate that.

52:19.937 --> 52:22.006
Congratulations,
Lane.

52:22.006 --> 52:23.974
There he is
politicking again.

52:23.974 --> 52:27.044
They act like
he hung the moon.

52:27.044 --> 52:28.813
[BOTH LAUGHING]

52:28.813 --> 52:30.915
MAN:
Hello, Kellie.

52:30.915 --> 52:32.617
How have you been?

52:32.617 --> 52:35.085
Hello, Martin.
How are you?

52:35.085 --> 52:37.355
Good.

52:37.355 --> 52:41.058
Ah, there you are.
Congratulations for Lane.

52:41.058 --> 52:42.993
Thank you.

52:42.993 --> 52:44.862
You did real well
in the roping.

52:44.862 --> 52:46.897
Yeah, yeah, I...

52:46.897 --> 52:48.866
won another buckle.

52:59.444 --> 53:03.514
KELLIE:
If you wanna go meet Tuff and
Cody and them, it's all right.

53:03.514 --> 53:07.218
I just have to get out
of these shoes.

53:10.988 --> 53:13.458
Can you help me with these?

53:22.300 --> 53:24.569
I'll be glad to get home.

53:24.569 --> 53:27.338
Two weeks in Vegas
is too long for me.

53:27.338 --> 53:30.107
Nobody made you come.

53:30.107 --> 53:32.410
Oh, I wanted
to see you ride.

53:32.410 --> 53:34.044
That's crap.
You hate bull riding.

53:34.044 --> 53:36.781
Calf roping's a little more
your style, isn't it?

53:36.781 --> 53:38.316
That's why you was talking
to Martin Hudson.

53:38.316 --> 53:39.617
'Course, you was
with him once.

53:39.617 --> 53:41.752
Maybe you ain't got it
out of your system.

53:41.752 --> 53:44.722
Lane, that was way before
we got together.

53:44.722 --> 53:47.625
So why was you
talking to him tonight?

53:47.625 --> 53:49.660
Well, I had to talk
to somebody.

53:49.660 --> 53:52.196
I don't want that jerk
anywheres near you, Kellie.

53:52.196 --> 53:54.064
Everybody knows
you done slept with him.

53:54.064 --> 53:56.066
Nobody knows.

53:56.066 --> 53:58.603
Lane, what's wrong?

53:58.603 --> 54:00.971
I am the world
champion now.

54:00.971 --> 54:02.540
People are looking at me.

54:02.540 --> 54:04.975
I want 'em thinking that
we got a great marriage.

54:06.744 --> 54:08.279
I thought we did.

54:13.351 --> 54:15.353
[***]

54:15.353 --> 54:17.488
[DOOR CLOSES]

54:35.940 --> 54:38.443
MAN [OVER TV]:
Tonight at the
National Finals Rodeo,

54:38.443 --> 54:40.478
the world champions
were crowned.

54:40.478 --> 54:43.448
Among them, the popular
bull rider Lane Frost,

54:43.448 --> 54:45.683
who won his first
national title.

54:45.683 --> 54:49.487
Here's a comment from
Frost's acceptance speech:

54:49.487 --> 54:51.722
LANE:
This is the biggest
dream of my life.

54:51.722 --> 54:54.191
Heck, it's the biggest
dream of any cowboy's life.

54:54.191 --> 54:57.862
Now that I'm world
champ, I'm gonna--

54:57.862 --> 55:01.466
I'm gonna do my best
for all the fans there, and...

55:01.466 --> 55:03.434
well, I just want
to thank everybody

55:03.434 --> 55:05.903
that stood behind me
on the way up.

55:05.903 --> 55:08.305
Thank you very much.

55:08.305 --> 55:10.441
[APPLAUSE]

55:19.984 --> 55:21.686
I'm sorry, Kel.

55:21.686 --> 55:23.488
I didn't mean to
take it out on you.

55:23.488 --> 55:25.556
It's just I got all these
people looking at me now

55:25.556 --> 55:27.024
and they all expect
something.

55:27.024 --> 55:29.226
I just don't want
to let 'em down.

55:29.226 --> 55:31.462
You won't, Lane.

55:31.462 --> 55:33.431
Yeah, but you
gotta help me.

55:33.431 --> 55:36.901
I will, honey.

55:36.901 --> 55:39.670
[***]

55:39.670 --> 55:43.340
I don't know why you
put up with me half the time.

55:48.813 --> 55:50.815
Real proud of you, Lane,
real proud of you.

55:50.815 --> 55:51.916
Thank you.
You, too, Kellie.

55:51.916 --> 55:53.918
Thank you.
How about it, everybody?

55:53.918 --> 55:57.755
Lane Frost, world champion
bull rider here.

55:57.755 --> 55:59.757
MAN:
Lane, Kellie gonna
meet us at Prescott's

55:59.757 --> 56:01.025
to promote that
hat deal of yours?

56:01.025 --> 56:02.993
LANE:
Nope. She had to
stay with her mom.

56:02.993 --> 56:05.496
MAN:
I got my Lane Frost underwear.
Got my Lane Frost lunch box.

56:05.496 --> 56:08.165
Ain't they coming out with some
boots with your name on 'em too?

56:08.165 --> 56:10.501
TUFF:
Yeah, they're calling
'em Puss In Boots.

56:10.501 --> 56:11.702
[LAUGHTER]

56:11.702 --> 56:13.904
[COUNTRY BAND PLAYING]

56:16.474 --> 56:21.412
* Well, I'm looking for eight
Lord, it's been a long time *

56:21.412 --> 56:25.115
* Yeah, I ride 'em high
And I ride 'em low *

56:25.115 --> 56:28.185
* The only life for me
That's the rodeo *

56:28.185 --> 56:31.489
* Got a pot of gold
Waiting in every town *

56:31.489 --> 56:33.691
* I gotta ride... *

56:33.691 --> 56:35.159
I gotta be heading out now,
y'all.

56:35.159 --> 56:37.061
There's plenty of my shirts
and my hats left

56:37.061 --> 56:38.829
if y'all have a mind
to buy 'em,

56:38.829 --> 56:40.631
and I do appreciate
your stopping by.

56:40.631 --> 56:43.033
Come on, Lane,
it's still early.

56:43.033 --> 56:45.235
We ain't even had
a dance yet, Lane.

56:45.235 --> 56:47.738
Pretty boys need
their sleep, too.

56:47.738 --> 56:50.808
Come on, Lane.
Just one more picture.

56:58.148 --> 56:59.917
[LINE RINGING]

56:59.917 --> 57:01.418
KELLIE [OVER PHONE]:
Hi, Lane.

57:01.418 --> 57:02.953
LANE:
Hey, darling. How you doing--

57:02.953 --> 57:04.689
Sorry I had to leave you
this message on the machine,

57:04.689 --> 57:06.390
but I waited as long as
I could, and Mom and me

57:06.390 --> 57:10.127
had to get started for Tulsa.
We'd be driving all night.

57:10.127 --> 57:12.362
I wish I could've
talked to you, honey.

57:12.362 --> 57:14.364
I love you. Bye.

57:14.364 --> 57:15.633
[BEEP]

57:15.633 --> 57:19.269
LANE:
Oh, shoot,
I thought you was there.

57:19.269 --> 57:22.272
I wish you was there. Um...

57:22.272 --> 57:23.774
I just got back, you know.

57:23.774 --> 57:26.310
I had one of them
promotional deals

57:26.310 --> 57:29.279
after the rodeo and they just
wouldn't let me go,

57:29.279 --> 57:31.281
all that stuff.

57:31.281 --> 57:34.619
Well, we're gonna go
to a few more rodeos,

57:34.619 --> 57:39.123
so, um, I guess I won't
be home till Friday night.

57:39.123 --> 57:41.926
Uh, if you get this,
leave me a number.

57:41.926 --> 57:46.163
I'll call you there
in Tulsa in the morning.

57:46.163 --> 57:50.167
I wish you was home.
Um, if not, I'll, uh, well,

57:50.167 --> 57:52.903
you know, I'll--
I'll call you tomorrow night.

57:52.903 --> 57:56.340
Okay, good luck with your
horse and everything.

57:56.340 --> 57:58.609
I love you.

57:58.609 --> 58:02.246
Um...good night.

58:28.573 --> 58:30.541
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

58:35.379 --> 58:36.714
Hi, Lane.

58:36.714 --> 58:39.083
I thought you might want
to have a nightcap.

58:39.083 --> 58:42.019
We don't even have
to go out.

58:42.019 --> 58:44.221
You know, I don't--
I don't drink much.

58:44.221 --> 58:45.923
Oh. Yeah, okay.

58:45.923 --> 58:48.926
Well, then maybe you can
sign this for my nephew.

58:48.926 --> 58:52.262
He's a real fan of yours.

58:52.262 --> 58:54.331
Okay. Sure.

58:54.331 --> 58:56.533
Ahem. Whew!

58:56.533 --> 59:00.270
It's not usually so cold
in Prescott this time of year.

59:00.270 --> 59:02.239
[CLEARS THROAT]

59:06.376 --> 59:10.014
All right, uh,
come on in a sec.

59:10.014 --> 59:11.682
Okay.

59:16.153 --> 59:17.655
[SIRENS]

59:20.057 --> 59:22.727
CODY:
You don't think anything's
happened to him, do you?

59:22.727 --> 59:24.461
TUFF:
I think one of them
buckle bunnies

59:24.461 --> 59:28.565
from last night was looking
to happen to him in a big way.

59:28.565 --> 59:30.000
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

59:30.000 --> 59:33.137
Listen to this:
It's called"Waiting on Lane."

59:33.137 --> 59:36.140
We've been waiting on Lane
Ever since we recall,

59:36.140 --> 59:38.308
We started in April
And it's coming on Fall,

59:38.308 --> 59:41.045
We have us a bite,
We have us a chew,

59:41.045 --> 59:43.648
We get us some shut eye,
We have us a brew,

59:43.648 --> 59:47.117
Someone's taking his picture,
Someone's wanting a loan

59:47.117 --> 59:50.688
He's kissing the babies
Or he's on the damn phone,

59:50.688 --> 59:53.758
But we'll keep on waiting,
Though we ain't pleased,

59:53.758 --> 59:56.661
'Cause the world champion
Bull rider's got the van keys!

59:56.661 --> 59:58.896
You're damn right!

59:58.896 --> 01:00:01.666
I liked that one.
[CODY SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:00:01.666 --> 01:00:02.967
How's your dog, Nelson?

01:00:02.967 --> 01:00:05.102
It ain't like that,
all right?

01:00:05.102 --> 01:00:07.905
I just--I was out and then
I ran into an uncle.

01:00:07.905 --> 01:00:10.307
Got a place outside of town,
it got too late,

01:00:10.307 --> 01:00:11.709
he couldn't drive me back.

01:00:14.011 --> 01:00:17.447
Wish I had me
an uncle like that.

01:00:17.447 --> 01:00:20.584
Put me up whenever
I come to town.

01:00:20.584 --> 01:00:22.152
Feed me.

01:00:22.152 --> 01:00:26.256
Then plant one of them big 'ol
greasy hickeys on my neck.

01:00:26.256 --> 01:00:28.192
[LAUGHING]

01:00:29.694 --> 01:00:31.195
Get in the van, Cletus.

01:00:35.165 --> 01:00:38.936
And then you drove from
Scottsdale to Prescott.

01:00:38.936 --> 01:00:42.239
What happened there?

01:00:42.239 --> 01:00:44.775
Tuff and Cody got a check
and I fell off.

01:00:44.775 --> 01:00:47.277
Then you drove
to Laramie?

01:00:52.049 --> 01:00:53.784
No.

01:00:56.186 --> 01:00:58.588
We stayed there.

01:00:58.588 --> 01:01:00.991
Drove back the next day.

01:01:15.472 --> 01:01:18.542
I missed you.

01:01:18.542 --> 01:01:21.345
Ah. I'm a little sore.

01:01:21.345 --> 01:01:24.514
Sorry.
You hurt?

01:01:24.514 --> 01:01:27.051
It's just the usual.

01:01:29.754 --> 01:01:32.122
KELLIE:
I'm glad you're home.

01:01:32.122 --> 01:01:35.359
Just wish it was
gonna be longer.

01:01:43.567 --> 01:01:46.136
That night in Prescott?

01:01:48.472 --> 01:01:49.974
KELLIE:
What?

01:01:59.483 --> 01:02:03.253
Too stupid to tell you.
It's just something Tuff did.

01:02:03.253 --> 01:02:06.423
I'll tell you when
I don't hurt so much.

01:02:09.359 --> 01:02:11.195
Night.

01:02:14.031 --> 01:02:15.766
Night.

01:02:26.844 --> 01:02:28.678
Want to thank you folks
for coming here today

01:02:28.678 --> 01:02:30.214
on such short notice.

01:02:30.214 --> 01:02:33.750
But Red Rock and I and Lane
have an important announcement.

01:02:33.750 --> 01:02:35.319
Lane's gonna try
the impossible--

01:02:35.319 --> 01:02:37.521
to ride the unridable bull
Red Rock.

01:02:37.521 --> 01:02:40.190
Red Rock hasn't been ridden
in 309 tries

01:02:40.190 --> 01:02:41.992
by the world's
toughest bull riders,

01:02:41.992 --> 01:02:43.160
including Lane.

01:02:43.160 --> 01:02:44.929
Lane'll get
three chances.

01:02:44.929 --> 01:02:48.432
The first one, April 17th,
right here in Sabine, Texas.

01:02:48.432 --> 01:02:51.368
If Lane succeeds, he'll write
his own page in rodeo history.

01:02:51.368 --> 01:02:53.237
Now, I'm sure you folks
have some questions

01:02:53.237 --> 01:02:54.905
and Lane and I'll be
glad to answer 'em for you.

01:02:54.905 --> 01:02:56.173
MAN:
Lane! Lane!

01:02:56.173 --> 01:02:57.741
LANE: Go and get you
something now, champ.

01:02:57.741 --> 01:02:59.709
Ah. No, thanks.
Appreciate it, though.

01:02:59.709 --> 01:03:00.945
No, take it.

01:03:00.945 --> 01:03:02.379
I watched you ride
ever since I was a kid.

01:03:02.379 --> 01:03:03.747
I always wanted to give you
something back.

01:03:03.747 --> 01:03:05.816
Well, I got a spot
for this. Thanks.

01:03:05.816 --> 01:03:08.052
Yeah.
Take care of yourself.

01:03:08.052 --> 01:03:10.154
Lane, why didn't you
tell me about this?

01:03:10.154 --> 01:03:12.189
You said we were coming
for a shirt promotion.

01:03:12.189 --> 01:03:14.691
Oh, well, I just wanted it
to be a surprise is all.

01:03:14.691 --> 01:03:16.193
We're partners, Lane.

01:03:16.193 --> 01:03:18.095
Well, of course we're
partners. I know that.

01:03:18.095 --> 01:03:19.363
What do you think
I'm doing this for?

01:03:19.363 --> 01:03:21.298
We got money, Lane.

01:03:21.298 --> 01:03:23.300
Well, he used to be
a world champion,

01:03:23.300 --> 01:03:24.534
he had him a little
bit of money.

01:03:24.534 --> 01:03:26.070
Now all he's got's
his hand out.

01:03:26.070 --> 01:03:27.304
I just don't want
that for us is the thing.

01:03:27.304 --> 01:03:29.406
We're never
gonna be like that.

01:03:29.406 --> 01:03:31.475
Well, shoot, I know.
Red Rock's my guarantee.

01:03:31.475 --> 01:03:33.277
Your guarantee is us.

01:03:33.277 --> 01:03:36.914
Of course it is, baby. What do
you think I'm doing this for?

01:03:36.914 --> 01:03:38.248
'Cause you like
all the attention

01:03:38.248 --> 01:03:40.417
and people
crowding around.

01:03:40.417 --> 01:03:42.219
So you don't have
to be alone with me.

01:03:42.219 --> 01:03:44.754
This is the most
important day of my life,

01:03:44.754 --> 01:03:46.290
and you're picking
a fight with me.

01:03:46.290 --> 01:03:48.758
Now I gotta go talk to some
of the people. You comin'?

01:03:48.758 --> 01:03:50.194
Not hardly.

01:03:56.400 --> 01:03:59.003
ELSIE:
We wanted to add on,
but we never had enough money.

01:03:59.003 --> 01:04:00.404
It's gonna be great,
Elsie.

01:04:00.404 --> 01:04:03.273
The corrals
that he's building for us

01:04:03.273 --> 01:04:05.209
are gonna be right up there.

01:04:05.209 --> 01:04:08.879
Lane's been
so good to us.

01:04:08.879 --> 01:04:10.948
I don't know where
he gets his energy.

01:04:10.948 --> 01:04:13.350
I've never seen him relax.

01:04:13.350 --> 01:04:15.585
We didn't even
have a honeymoon.

01:04:15.585 --> 01:04:17.021
We did.

01:04:17.021 --> 01:04:19.924
Clyde didn't talk to me
for the first three days.

01:04:19.924 --> 01:04:21.425
On your honeymoon?

01:04:21.425 --> 01:04:23.327
Finally I went to him
and said,

01:04:23.327 --> 01:04:26.030
"What is wrong?
What have I done?"

01:04:26.030 --> 01:04:27.564
You know what he said?

01:04:27.564 --> 01:04:29.533
"They ruined my boots."

01:04:29.533 --> 01:04:31.168
His boots?

01:04:31.168 --> 01:04:33.037
Yeah,
on the wedding day.

01:04:33.037 --> 01:04:35.472
Some of his friends threw him
into the water trough.

01:04:35.472 --> 01:04:40.410
It was, you know, just a joke,
but he worried and brooded.

01:04:40.410 --> 01:04:42.246
It's funny now.

01:04:42.246 --> 01:04:45.215
I see a lot of Clyde in Lane.

01:04:45.215 --> 01:04:46.416
But he's
a good man.

01:04:46.416 --> 01:04:49.253
I couldn't have asked
for better.

01:04:49.253 --> 01:04:51.989
Oh, heck, fellas. Why didn't you
tell me we was driving
to Spanish Fork?

01:04:51.989 --> 01:04:53.690
I told Kellie we was
flying there in the morning.

01:04:53.690 --> 01:04:56.593
Tomorrow's flight's
all full. Sorry, Kel.

01:04:56.593 --> 01:04:57.727
Lane, it's all right.

01:04:57.727 --> 01:04:59.563
No, it ain't.
She drove all the way up here!

01:04:59.563 --> 01:05:01.498
TUFF:
Gotta go, gotta go, gotta rodeo!

01:05:01.498 --> 01:05:04.368
I got to see you ride.
You needed clean clothes
anyway.

01:05:04.368 --> 01:05:06.370
Just give me
your dirty things.

01:05:06.370 --> 01:05:08.038
If Spanish Fork wasn't
big money,

01:05:08.038 --> 01:05:09.806
I'd turn around
and stay with you.

01:05:09.806 --> 01:05:11.008
Don't worry about it.

01:05:11.008 --> 01:05:12.509
At least I got to see you
for a bit.

01:05:12.509 --> 01:05:13.978
I'll call you
in the morning.

01:05:13.978 --> 01:05:16.013
I love you.

01:05:16.013 --> 01:05:17.647
[ENGINE RUNNING]

01:05:26.790 --> 01:05:27.857
MAN:
Kellie?

01:05:27.857 --> 01:05:29.126
Martin. Hi.

01:05:29.126 --> 01:05:32.929
Oh, I just drove
up to see Lane. Uh. Thanks.

01:05:32.929 --> 01:05:34.464
You'd figure world champion,

01:05:34.464 --> 01:05:36.800
he could get somebody
to do his laundry for him.

01:05:36.800 --> 01:05:39.503
I don't mind.
That way, it's done right.

01:05:39.503 --> 01:05:42.739
Hey, um...
want to get some dinner?

01:05:42.739 --> 01:05:46.843
Thanks, but I should go.
I got a million things to do.

01:05:46.843 --> 01:05:49.379
Lane's been gone so much,
it's really hard to keep up.

01:05:49.379 --> 01:05:51.381
If I leave now,
I'll get back by 11.

01:05:51.381 --> 01:05:52.616
It was good to see you,
Martin.

01:05:52.616 --> 01:05:54.518
Now, it's good
seeing you too, Kellie.

01:06:00.590 --> 01:06:02.526
Can I change my mind?

01:06:05.462 --> 01:06:08.498
