All them things I said, I should
have been saying to myself.

01:20:48.077 --> 01:20:50.413
I'm sorry, Kel.

01:20:52.515 --> 01:20:54.850
I love you, Kel.

01:20:57.853 --> 01:21:00.256
I don't want it anymore.

01:21:00.256 --> 01:21:02.058
I just wanna spend
my time with you.

01:21:02.058 --> 01:21:04.627
I wanna wake up with you
in the morning in a real house,

01:21:04.627 --> 01:21:08.231
and know that I don't gotta
go somewhere to a damn rodeo.

01:21:08.231 --> 01:21:11.334
That's what I want,
too, Lane.

01:21:13.136 --> 01:21:16.405
I'll make it up to you, Kel.
I love you.

01:21:16.405 --> 01:21:18.541
I love you, Lane.

01:21:18.541 --> 01:21:20.476
I love you.

01:21:22.912 --> 01:21:24.713
ANNOUNCER:
Every eye is on this young man.

01:21:24.713 --> 01:21:28.351
This is his third and final try
at riding Red Rock.

01:21:28.351 --> 01:21:32.788
Now, the bull that has bucked
off 311 cowboys...

01:21:32.788 --> 01:21:34.958
Bear down there, Lane.
This rope right here is perfect.

01:21:34.958 --> 01:21:38.861
ANNOUNCER:
This is truly a challenge
of the champions...

01:21:38.861 --> 01:21:41.564
Eight seconds will
put you over the top.

01:21:41.564 --> 01:21:43.366
Okay, boys. Okay, boys!

01:21:43.366 --> 01:21:45.168
Here it is.

01:21:45.168 --> 01:21:47.736
Will this be the first man
in rodeo history

01:21:47.736 --> 01:21:49.905
to ever ride Red Rock?

01:21:49.905 --> 01:21:51.240
Go, Lane!

01:21:51.240 --> 01:21:52.675
Look at this bull!

01:21:52.675 --> 01:21:54.510
I've never seen anyone
try it four times...

01:21:54.510 --> 01:21:57.013
[CONTINUES SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

01:21:58.747 --> 01:22:00.383
Stay with him.

01:22:00.383 --> 01:22:01.817
Ride him!

01:22:01.817 --> 01:22:04.587
Yeah!
He got him! Yeah!

01:22:09.725 --> 01:22:11.660
[BUZZER]

01:22:13.696 --> 01:22:18.101
ANNOUNCER:
Lane Frost is the first man to
ride Red Rock to the whistle.

01:22:18.101 --> 01:22:22.638
Boy, oh, boy,
not since Freckles Brown
rode Tornado in 1967

01:22:22.638 --> 01:22:26.309
has there been a ride
to match this.

01:22:29.045 --> 01:22:31.547
Lane,
you just won your own page

01:22:31.547 --> 01:22:34.417
in rodeo history.

01:22:41.524 --> 01:22:44.293
LANE:
Shoot, darling, I ain't
been on a bus since April.

01:22:44.293 --> 01:22:45.694
Heck, I probably
wouldn't go now

01:22:45.694 --> 01:22:48.497
except everybody's
expecting me up to Cheyenne.

01:22:48.497 --> 01:22:50.699
Tuff, why he's fixing to get
one of them little planes.

01:22:50.699 --> 01:22:53.736
Maybe I'll drive up there
and meet you.

01:22:53.736 --> 01:22:55.171
Well, hey,
I got a nice hotel.

01:22:55.171 --> 01:22:57.240
You know, maybe we could
get us one of them suites,

01:22:57.240 --> 01:22:59.175
you know, with
the big old bubbling tub

01:22:59.175 --> 01:23:00.576
and a king-size bed.

01:23:00.576 --> 01:23:04.580
Yeah? How many cowboys
are gonna be sleeping with us?

01:23:04.580 --> 01:23:08.751
Just Tuff and Cody.
'Course they'd stay
in another room.

01:23:10.919 --> 01:23:12.955
Breeze feels nice, huh?

01:23:12.955 --> 01:23:14.323
Yeah.

01:23:14.323 --> 01:23:16.592
Just a little further
on up here.

01:23:16.592 --> 01:23:20.429
Never ridden a horse
with a blindfold before.

01:23:20.429 --> 01:23:21.764
Oh.

01:23:21.764 --> 01:23:26.535
Okay, just a little further,
a little further. There you go.

01:23:29.338 --> 01:23:31.774
KELLIE:
Oh, Lane.

01:23:31.774 --> 01:23:33.709
It's beautiful.

01:23:33.709 --> 01:23:37.012
LANE:
See? I'll build your
corrals right up there.

01:23:37.012 --> 01:23:39.682
Then up there on top of the hill
there, I'm gonna put me

01:23:39.682 --> 01:23:42.251
some bucket chutes, I can
have me a bull riding school

01:23:42.251 --> 01:23:43.886
and come on over here.

01:23:43.886 --> 01:23:45.088
Build you a great,
big old house

01:23:45.088 --> 01:23:46.689
right up there
on top of that hill.

01:23:46.689 --> 01:23:49.225
Big house.
Lots of kids running around.

01:23:49.225 --> 01:23:50.659
Right over here,

01:23:50.659 --> 01:23:53.196
I'm gonna put that trailer
with a big guitar on it.

01:23:53.196 --> 01:23:55.398
Ha. You're kidding,
aren't you?

01:23:55.398 --> 01:23:56.665
No, I ain't kidding.

01:23:56.665 --> 01:23:59.402
Wouldn't seem like home
otherwise.

01:23:59.402 --> 01:24:01.937
Please, tell me
you're making a joke, Lane.

01:24:01.937 --> 01:24:04.740
Yes, darling.
I'm making a joke.

01:24:04.740 --> 01:24:07.376
I'm gonna put it right over
there next to your corrals.

01:24:07.376 --> 01:24:08.577
Ha, ha!

01:24:15.184 --> 01:24:17.786
[PLANE ENGINE BUZZING]

01:24:22.258 --> 01:24:24.059
Hey, Cody, why don't you
read us one of them poems?

01:24:24.059 --> 01:24:26.295
If I'm gonna puke,
I'd like to have a good reason.

01:24:26.295 --> 01:24:29.932
I ain't got but one new one.
That's all right.

01:24:29.932 --> 01:24:32.968
There's a hundred years
Of history and 104 of that

01:24:32.968 --> 01:24:36.339
All gathered into thinking
Going on beneath his hat.

01:24:36.339 --> 01:24:41.610
The cold flame burns within him
Till his skin's as cold as ice.

01:24:41.610 --> 01:24:46.249
And the dues he paid to get
Here are worth every sacrifice.

01:24:46.249 --> 01:24:48.417
All the miles spent,
Sleepy driving,

01:24:48.417 --> 01:24:50.619
All the money down the drain.

01:24:50.619 --> 01:24:55.758
All the "if I's" and "nearlys,"
All the bandages and pain.

01:24:55.758 --> 01:25:00.663
All the female tears left dry
And all the fever and the fight

01:25:00.663 --> 01:25:04.500
Are just a small down payment
On the ride he makes tonight.

01:25:04.500 --> 01:25:08.003
It's guts and love and glory.

01:25:08.003 --> 01:25:10.473
One mortal's chance at fame.

01:25:10.473 --> 01:25:13.542
His legacy is rodeo,

01:25:13.542 --> 01:25:17.045
And cowboy is his name.

01:25:17.045 --> 01:25:18.847
There it is, boys.

01:25:18.847 --> 01:25:20.983
The dad, all right.

01:25:20.983 --> 01:25:23.586
Yep,
he's the daddy of them all.

01:25:23.586 --> 01:25:25.988
What do you say, boys?
Let's go get some money.

01:25:25.988 --> 01:25:29.425
ANNOUNCER:
Bull riding in Cheyenne,
Wyoming...

01:25:29.425 --> 01:25:33.196
You gonna be a bull rider, Cody?
Yes, sir.

01:25:34.497 --> 01:25:36.865
What's your name?
Brandon.

01:25:36.865 --> 01:25:38.834
CODY:
Lane.

01:25:38.834 --> 01:25:41.704
Looks like Tuff got tired
of being a hard-ass.

01:25:49.912 --> 01:25:51.914
KELLIE:
Lane. Lane!

01:25:51.914 --> 01:25:54.950
ANNOUNCER:
We're looking at some kind
of rank bull-riding

01:25:54.950 --> 01:25:56.385
here at Old Cheyenne.

01:25:56.385 --> 01:25:58.387
I think you're gonna have
to be in the 90s

01:25:58.387 --> 01:26:00.389
to get a piece of this thing.

01:26:00.389 --> 01:26:02.558
There's no doubt this man

01:26:02.558 --> 01:26:04.560
is an in-house favorite
here today.

01:26:04.560 --> 01:26:07.930
This is Lane Frost of Oklahoma.
Seven times...

01:26:07.930 --> 01:26:09.965
Whoa!
Ooh.

01:26:09.965 --> 01:26:11.400
No need to be rude.
Slack.

01:26:11.400 --> 01:26:13.902
[BULL BELLOWING]

01:26:13.902 --> 01:26:17.373
CODY:
Let's win some money, now.
Let's win some money.

01:26:17.373 --> 01:26:19.708
You ride him, champ.
Look out, boys! All Right!

01:26:22.978 --> 01:26:25.314
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:26:30.919 --> 01:26:34.557
ANNOUNCER:
Lane Frost
is gonna ride this bull!

01:26:36.959 --> 01:26:38.527
Whoo!

01:26:43.599 --> 01:26:49.171
Friends, this may be the ride
of the year that we're
watching right here!

01:26:49.171 --> 01:26:51.173
KELLIE: Go, Lane!

01:26:51.173 --> 01:26:52.675
[BUZZER]
All right!

01:26:55.844 --> 01:26:57.646
There you go,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:26:57.646 --> 01:27:02.751
You have just watched some kind
of a great bull ride...

01:27:06.522 --> 01:27:08.757
Aah!

01:27:08.757 --> 01:27:11.260
A nasty punch from that bull!

01:27:11.260 --> 01:27:13.696
This man may be hurt.

01:27:13.696 --> 01:27:16.299
Lane!

01:27:16.299 --> 01:27:19.868
I do hope this is not an injury
of a serious nature...

01:27:19.868 --> 01:27:21.504
[***]

01:27:31.980 --> 01:27:34.016
[***]

