ELSIE:
Clyde?

01:28:04.513 --> 01:28:08.050
I've been sitting here,
trying to remember

01:28:08.050 --> 01:28:10.319
if I ever told him...

01:28:14.423 --> 01:28:18.026
I told him I was proud of him.

01:28:18.026 --> 01:28:20.363
I know...

01:28:22.331 --> 01:28:25.334
That he did a good job.

01:28:30.038 --> 01:28:32.307
But I...

01:28:34.443 --> 01:28:36.945
I can't remember...

01:28:39.181 --> 01:28:41.684
a single time...

01:28:43.118 --> 01:28:45.521
I told him...

01:28:48.056 --> 01:28:50.426
I loved him.

01:28:58.033 --> 01:28:59.868
TUFF:
Kellie?

01:29:01.737 --> 01:29:04.473
Hi, Tuff.

01:29:04.473 --> 01:29:06.241
It's warming up a bit.

01:29:06.241 --> 01:29:07.309
Yeah.

01:29:07.309 --> 01:29:09.445
Think so.

01:29:14.349 --> 01:29:18.754
They're giving a special award
for Lane at the finals.

01:29:20.188 --> 01:29:23.058
They want you
to accept it.

01:29:33.936 --> 01:29:35.804
You do it, Tuff.

01:29:35.804 --> 01:29:38.741
TUFF:
They'd like for you
to be there, Kellie.

01:29:46.214 --> 01:29:49.618
I have to start
a new life, Tuff.

01:29:51.086 --> 01:29:53.288
I'm going back to school.

01:29:53.288 --> 01:29:56.425
I'm trying to make
some plans.

01:29:58.594 --> 01:30:02.164
It's just too hard
to be around rodeo right now.

01:30:13.976 --> 01:30:17.012
Back in the spring,
Lane said...

01:30:18.981 --> 01:30:21.216
"This is your year."

01:30:21.216 --> 01:30:23.151
That...

01:30:23.151 --> 01:30:26.188
I'd win the championship.

01:30:30.158 --> 01:30:33.428
I told him
he was full of it.

01:30:39.902 --> 01:30:43.939
Now it's only
a week away and...

01:30:43.939 --> 01:30:46.975
I really think
that I got a chance.

01:30:55.718 --> 01:30:59.488
I never had anybody
believe that much in me.

01:31:06.194 --> 01:31:09.698
He really loved you, Tuff.

01:31:24.780 --> 01:31:27.282
ANNOUNCER:
It's been in the papers,
you've seen it on TV,

01:31:27.282 --> 01:31:30.085
Tuff Hedeman has declared that
he will win the world title

01:31:30.085 --> 01:31:33.155
in memory of his
fallen partner, Lane Frost.

01:31:33.155 --> 01:31:36.692
And remember, Frost was killed
last summer at Cheyenne,

01:31:36.692 --> 01:31:38.827
when a broken rib
pierced his heart.

01:31:38.827 --> 01:31:40.929
Now, Tuff is dedicating this,
his last ride,

01:31:40.929 --> 01:31:42.230
in memory of his friend.

01:31:42.230 --> 01:31:43.465
Okay, boys!

01:31:43.465 --> 01:31:45.901
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

01:31:47.402 --> 01:31:50.272
ANNOUNCER:
Great little bull ride
started here.

01:31:54.610 --> 01:31:58.914
ANNOUNCER:
Look at this! He's proving
what he said he can do!

01:31:58.914 --> 01:32:00.248
[BUZZER]

01:32:00.248 --> 01:32:02.250
He did it! What a bull ride!

01:32:02.250 --> 01:32:05.187
We'll have that score
coming up for Tuff Hedeman.

01:32:05.187 --> 01:32:06.188
Is he hung up?

01:32:07.823 --> 01:32:10.959
KELLIE: No.
He's riding for Lane now.

01:32:12.094 --> 01:32:14.296
ANNOUNCER:
Remember, he dedicated it.

01:32:14.296 --> 01:32:17.666
I'll betcha somebody's smiling
upstairs right now!

01:32:17.666 --> 01:32:19.635
Ride him!

01:32:19.635 --> 01:32:22.004
ANNOUNCER:
Lane Frost, he's riding
for you, my friend.

01:32:24.039 --> 01:32:26.308
[***]

01:32:43.025 --> 01:32:48.163
Ninety-one points,
our new world champion cowboy.

01:32:50.432 --> 01:32:52.567
[***]

